{"title_page": "Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Court in Bangladesh", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=January 2019}}\n{{Politics of Bangladesh}}\n'''Chief Metropolitan Magistrate court''' is a type of [[Metropolitan Magistrate Courts of Bangladesh|Metropolitan Magistrate Court]] which is found in the metropolitan cities of Bangladesh. These courts are presided by the '''Chief Metropolitan Magistrate''' as per the Code of Criminal Procedure of Bangladesh. These courts are under the control to the [[Metropolitan Session Court in Bangladesh|Metropolitan Session Judge Courts]].<ref name=\"SO\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14311|title=Subordination of Executive,Judicial and Metropolitan Magistrates- bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref>\nThe amended form of the [[Criminal procedure|Criminal Procedure]] Code gives the government the power to appoint a Chief Metropolitan Magistrate and other magistrates in a metropolitan area.<ref name=\"CSC\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14288|title=Classes of Session Court|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref> The provision of recruitment of one or more Additional Chief Metropolitan Magistrates is also directed.\n\n==Jurisdiction==\nTo adhere to the Code of Criminal Procedure, the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, with the pre-approval of the government, has been given power<ref name=\"CMM\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14317|title=Chief Metropolitan Magistrate&nbsp;\u2013 bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref>\n\n*To conduct and distribute the business and the practice in the courts of metropolitan magistrates\n*To form a bench of metropolitan magistrates;\n*To set the time and place of the session of the bench;\n*To remove any difference between metropolitan magistrates that may arise during the session, and\n*To forward any matter that can be dealt by the [[District magistrate|District Magistrate]] under His/Her subordination.\n\n===Scope of penalty===\nAccording to Metropolitan Police [[statute|Act]], only a criminal case can be brought under the court trial based on a written report of a police officer.<ref name=\"MC\">{{Cite web|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Metropolitan_Court|title=Metropolitan Court&nbsp;\u2013 Banglapedia|website=en.banglapedia.org|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref> The powers of the Metropolitan Magistrate include [[imprisonment]] for a maximum of five years, a solitary confinement is authorized by law, fine not exceeding taka 10,000 and the order of whipping.<ref name=\"Sen\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14348|title=Sentences which Magistrates may pass&nbsp;\u2013 bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Government of Bangladesh}}\n{{Judiciaries of Asia}}\n\n[[Category:Judiciary of Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi law]]\n[[Category:Politics of Bangladesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Underlinked|date=January 2019}}\n{{Politics of Bangladesh}}\n'''Chief Metropolitan Magistrate court''' is a type of [[Metropolitan Magistrate Courts of Bangladesh|Metropolitan Magistrate Court]] which is found in the metropolitan cities of Bangladesh. These courts are presided by the '''Chief Metropolitan Magistrate''' as per the Code of Criminal Procedure of Bangladesh. These courts are under the control to the [[Metropolitan Session Court in Bangladesh|Metropolitan Session Judge Courts]].<ref name=\"SO\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14311|title=Subordination of Executive,Judicial and Metropolitan Magistrates- bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref>\nThe amended form of the [[Criminal procedure|Criminal Procedure]] Code gives the government the power to appoint a Chief Metropolitan Magistrate and other magistrates in a metropolitan area.<ref name=\"CSC\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14288|title=Classes of Session Court|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref> The provision of recruitment of one or more Additional Chief Metropolitan Magistrates is also directed.\n\n==Jurisdiction==\nTo adhere to the Code of Criminal Procedure, the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, with the pre-approval of the government, has been given power<ref name=\"CMM\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14317|title=Chief Metropolitan Magistrate&nbsp;\u2013 bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref>\n\n*To conduct and distribute the business and the practice in the courts of metropolitan magistrates\n*To form a bench of metropolitan magistrates;\n*To set the time and place of the session of the bench;\n*To remove any difference between metropolitan magistrates that may arise during the session, and\n*To forward any matter that can be dealt by the [[District magistrate|District Magistrate]] under His/Her subordination.\n\n===Scope of penalty===\nAccording to Metropolitan Police [[Act]], only a criminal case can be brought under the court trial based on a written report of a police officer.<ref name=\"MC\">{{Cite web|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Metropolitan_Court|title=Metropolitan Court&nbsp;\u2013 Banglapedia|website=en.banglapedia.org|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref> The powers of the Metropolitan Magistrate include [[imprisonment]] for a maximum of five years, a solitary confinement is authorized by law, fine not exceeding taka 10,000 and the order of whipping.<ref name=\"Sen\">{{Cite web|url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/print_sections.php?id=75&vol=&sections_id=14348|title=Sentences which Magistrates may pass&nbsp;\u2013 bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|website=bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2018-05-04}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Government of Bangladesh}}\n{{Judiciaries of Asia}}\n\n[[Category:Judiciary of Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi law]]\n[[Category:Politics of Bangladesh]]\n", "name_user": "Squids and Chips", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eScope of penalty:disambiguate Act", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_Metropolitan_Magistrate_Court_in_Bangladesh"}
{"title_page": "Gillnetting", "text_new": "[[File:Eilif Peterssen-Laksefiskeren (1889).jpg|thumb|300px|right|Oil painting of gillnetting, ''The salmon fisher'' by [[Eilif Peterssen]].]]\n\n'''Gillnetting''' is a common fishing method used by [[fishing industry|commercial]] and [[Artisanal fishing|artisanal]] fishers of all the oceans and in some freshwater and estuary areas. Gill nets are composed of vertical panels of netting that hang from a line with regularly spaced floaters that hold the line on the surface of the water. The floats are sometimes called \"corks\" and the line with corks is generally referred to as a \"cork line.\" The line along the bottom of the panels is generally weighted. Traditionally this line has been weighted with lead and may be referred to as  \"lead line.\"  A gill net is normally set in a straight line. Gill nets can be characterized by mesh size, as well as colour and type of filament from which they are made. Fish may be caught by gill nets in three ways:\n\n# Wedged&nbsp;\u2013 held by the mesh around the body.\n# Gilled&nbsp;\u2013 held by mesh slipping behind the [[operculum (fish)|opercula]].\n# Tangled&nbsp;\u2013 held by teeth, spines, [[maxilla|maxillaries]], or other protrusions without the body penetrating the mesh.\n\nMost often fish are gilled. A fish swims into a net and passes only part way through the mesh. When it struggles to free itself, the twine slips behind the gill cover and prevents escape.<ref>Murphy, B. and Willis, D. (1996) [http://www.afsbooks.org/x55029xm \"Fisheries Techniques: Second edition.\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221024307/http://afsbooks.org/x55029xm |date=2013-02-21 }} Bethesda, MD: American Fisheries Society.</ref>\n\nGillnets are so effective that their use is closely monitored and regulated by fisheries management and [[enforcement]] agencies. [[Mesh size]], twine strength, as well as net length and depth are all closely regulated to reduce [[bycatch]] of non-target species. Gillnets have a high degree of size selectivity. Most [[Salmon#Salmon fisheries|salmon fisheries]] in particular have an extremely low incidence of catching non-target species.<ref>[http://www.dfw.state.or.us/fish/OSCRP/CRM/docs/Selective_Fisheries_JN_071220.pdf Selective Fisheries] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224930/http://www.dfw.state.or.us/fish/OSCRP/CRM/docs/Selective_Fisheries_JN_071220.pdf |date=2016-03-03 }} ''Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife''. Retrieved 26 September 2014.</ref>\n[[File:BC Bow Picker Mahalo Kai (Commercial Salmon Gillnetter).jpg|alt=image of a commercial salmon bow picker, Mahalo Kai; drum holding net is located in the bow of the boat. The cabin is in the rear.|thumb|Contemporary Canadian commercial salmon bowpicker on trailer.  Gillnet is evident on the metal drum in the bow of the boat. ]]\nA fishing vessel rigged to fish by gillnetting is a '''gillnetter'''. A gillnetter which deploys its gillnet from the [[Bow (ship)|bow]] is a '''[[:File:BC Bow Picker Mahalo Kai (Commercial Salmon Gillnetter).jpg|bowpicker]]''', while one which deploys its gillnet from the [[stern]] is a '''sternpicker'''.\n\n==History==\n{{see also|History of fishing}}\n[[File:Fish and Wildlife Service worker on boat checking gill net full of fish.jpg|thumb|[[Fish and Wildlife Service]] worker on boat checking gillnet full of fish.]]\n\nGillnets existed in ancient times, as archaeological evidence from the Middle East demonstrates.<ref>Nun, Mendel (1989). ''The Sea of Galilee and Its Fishermen in the New Testament,'' pp. 28-44. Kibbutz Ein Gev, Kinnereth Sailing Co.</ref> In North America, Native American fishermen used cedar canoes and natural fibre nets, e.g., made with nettles or the inner bark of cedar.<ref>Stewart, Hilary (1977). ''Indian Fishing: Early Methods on the Northwest Coast,'' p.79 in 1st paperback edition, 1982. Seattle, University of Washington Press.</ref> They would attach stones to the bottom of the nets as weights, and pieces of wood to the top, to use as floats. This allowed the net to suspend straight up and down in the water. Each net would be suspended either from shore or between two boats. Native fishers in the Pacific Northwest, Canada, and Alaska still commonly use gillnets in their fisheries for [[salmon]] and [[Rainbow trout|steelhead]].\n\nBoth drift gillnets and setnets have long been used by cultures around the world. There is evidence of fisheries exploitation, including gillnetting, going far back in Japanese history, with many specific details available from the [[Edo period]] (1603\u20131868).<ref>Ruddle, Kenneth and Akimich, Tomoya. \"Sea Tenure in Japan and the Southwestern Ryukyus,\" in Cordell, John, Ed. (1989), ''A Sea of Small Boats'', pp. 337-370. Cambridge, Mass., Cultural Survival, Inc.</ref> Fisheries in the [[Shetland]] Islands, which were settled by [[Norsemen]] during the [[Viking age]], share cultural and technological similarities with Norwegian fisheries, including gillnet fisheries for herring.<ref>Goodlad, C.A. (1970). ''Shetland Fishing Saga'', pp. 59-60. The Shetland Times, Ltd.</ref> Many of the Norwegian immigrant fishermen who came to fish in the great Columbia River salmon fishery during the second half of the 19th century did so because they had experience in the gillnet fishery for cod in the waters surrounding the [[Lofoten]] Islands of northern [[Norway]].<ref>Martin, Irene (1994). ''Legacy and Testament: The Story of the Columbia River Gillnetter'', p. 38. Pullman, Washington State University Press.</ref> Gillnets were used as part of the seasonal round by [[Sweden|Swedish]] fishermen as well.<ref>Lofgen, Ovar. \"Marine Ecotypes in Preindustrial Sweden: A Comparative Discussion of Swedish Peasant Fishermen,\" in Andersen, Raoul, Ed. (1979), ''North Atlantic Maritime Cultures'', pp. 83-109. The Hague, Mouton.</ref> Welsh and English fishermen gillnetted for Atlantic salmon in the rivers of [[Wales]] and [[England]] in [[coracle]]s, using hand-made nets, for at least several centuries.<ref>Jenkins, J. Geraint (1974). ''Nets and Coracles'', p. 68. London, David and Charles.</ref> These are but a few of the examples of historic gillnet fisheries around the world.\n\nGillnetting was an early fishing technology in colonial America,{{vague|reason=\"Colonial America\" is not a [[proper name]] of any region. (But \"colonial America\" is ambiguous among (at least) the New World, the 13 Colonies, and North America north of the [[Rio Grande]]|date=February 2018}} used for example, in fisheries for Atlantic salmon and shad.<ref>Netboy, Anthony (1973) ''The Salmon: Their Fight for Survival,'' pp. 181-182. Boston, Houghton Mifflin.</ref> Immigrant fishermen from northern Europe and the Mediterranean brought a number of different adaptations of the technology from their respective homelands with them to the rapidly expanding salmon fisheries of the Columbia River from the 1860s onward.<ref>Martin, 1994, p. 44.</ref> The boats used by these fisherman were typically around {{convert|25|ft|m|0}} long and powered by oars. Many of these boats also had small sails and were called \"row-sail\" boats. At the beginning of the 1900s, steam powered ships would haul these smaller boats to their fishing grounds and retrieve them at the end of each day. However, at that time [[gasoline|gas]] powered boats were beginning to make their appearance, and by the 1930s, the row-sail boat had virtually disappeared, except in Bristol Bay, Alaska, where motors were prohibited in the gillnet fishery by territorial law until 1951.<ref>Andrews, Ralph W. and Larsen, A.K. (1959). ''Fish and Ships'', p. 108. Seattle, Superior Publishing Co.</ref>\n[[File:MENDING A GILLNET ON THE DOCK AT ST. HELENS ON THE COLUMBIA RIVER - NARA - 548102.jpg|right|thumb|A fisherman repairs a gillnet (April 1973, [[St. Helens, Oregon]])]]\n\nIn 1931, the first powered drum was created by Laurie Jarelainen.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}} The drum is a circular device that is set to the side of the boat and draws in the nets. The powered drum allowed the nets to be drawn in much faster and along with the faster gas powered boats, fisherman were able to fish in areas they had previously been unable to go into, thereby revolutionizing the fishing industry.\n\nDuring World War II, navigation and communication devices, as well as many other forms of maritime equipment (ex. depth-sounding and radar) were improved and made more compact. These devices became much more accessible to the average fisherman, thus making their range and mobility increasingly larger. It also served to make the industry much more competitive, as the fisherman were forced to invest more in boats and equipment to stay current with developing technology.\n\nThe introduction of fine [[synthetic fibre]]s such as [[nylon]] in the construction of fishing gear during the 1960s marked an expansion in the commercial use of gillnets. The new materials were cheaper and easier to handle, lasted longer and required less maintenance than natural fibres. In addition, [[Multifilament fishing line|multifilament nylon]], [[Monofilament fishing line|monofilament]] or [[Braided fishing line|multimonofilament fibres]] become almost invisible in water, so nets made with synthetic twines generally caught greater numbers of fish than natural fibre nets used in comparable situations.\n\nNylon is highly resistant to abrasion and degradation, hence the netting has the potential to last for many years if it is not recovered. This [[ghost fishing]] is of environmental concern. Attaching the gillnet floats with biodegradable material can reduce the problem.<ref name=\"gillnet\"/> However it is difficult to generalize about the longevity of ghost-fishing gillnets due to the varying environments in which they are used. Some researchers have found gill-nets still catching fish and crustaceans over a year after loss{{ref|Kaiser}}, while others have found lost nets destroyed by wave action within one month{{ref|Puente}} or overgrown with [[seaweed]]s, increasing their visibility and reducing their catching potential to such an extent that they became a microhabitat used by small fish.{{ref|Erzini}}\n\nThis type of net was heavily used by many [[Japan]]ese, [[South Korea]]n, and [[Taiwan]]ese fishing fleets on the high seas in the 1980s to target [[tuna]]s. Although highly selective with respect to size class of animals captured, gillnets are associated with high numbers of incidental captures of [[cetacea]]ns ([[whale]]s and [[dolphin]]s). In the Sri Lankan gillnet fishery, one dolphin is caught for every 1.7\u20134.0 tonnes of tuna landed{{ref|Hall}}. This compares poorly with the rate of one dolphin per 70 tonnes of tuna landed in the eastern Pacific [[purse seine]] tuna fishery.\n\nMany types of gillnets are used by [[Fisheries science|fisheries scientists]] to monitor fish populations.<ref>Bruce Crawford. \"Variable Mesh Gill Nets (in Lakes).\" In Johnson, David, et al. ''Salmonid Field Protocols Handbook''. Bethesda, Maryland, American Fisheries Society, 2007, pp. 425-433.</ref> Vertical gillnets are designed to allow scientists to determine the depth distribution of the captured fish.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Lackey |first1=Robert |title=Vertical gill nets for studying depth distribution of small fish |journal=Transactions of the American Fisheries Society |date=1968 |volume=97 |issue=3 |page=296-299 |doi=https://doi.org/10.1577/1548-8659(1968)97[296:VGNFSD]2.0.CO;2 |url=https://doi.org/10.1577/1548-8659(1968)97[296:VGNFSD]2.0.CO;2}}</ref>\n\n==Legal status==\n[[United Nations General Assembly]] Resolution 46/215<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/documents/ga/res/46/a46r215|title=A/RES/46/215.  Large-scale pelagic drift-net fishing and its impact on the living marine resources of the world's oceans and seas|author=|date=|website=www.un.org|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref> called for the cessation of all \"large-scale pelagic drift-net fishing\" in [[international waters]] by the end of 1992.  The laws of individual countries vary with regard to fishing in waters under their jurisdiction.\n\nPossession of gillnets is illegal in some U.S. states and heavily regulated in others.\n\nOregon voters had the chance to decide on whether gillnetting will continue in the [[Columbia River]] in November 2012 by voting on Measure 81.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yes on Measure 81 Stop Gillnetting|url=http://www.stopgillnetting.com/|accessdate=14 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120814002555/http://www.stopgillnetting.com/|archive-date=14 August 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The measure was defeated with 65% of Oregon voters voting against the measure and allowing commercial gillnet fishing to continue on the Columbia River.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sos.oregon.gov/elections/Documents/results/results-11-2012.pdf|title=Oregon Secretary of State: Official Results November 2012 General Election|author=|date=|website=sos.oregon.gov|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Columbia River Basin is currently under a management agreement that spans from 2008 to December 31, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=NOAA Fisheries West Coast Region|title=Environmental Impact Statement for Programmatic Review of Harvest Actions for Salmon and Steelhead in the Columbia Basin related to U.S. v. Oregon :: NOAA Fisheries West Coast Region |url=http://www.westcoast.fisheries.noaa.gov/fisheries/salmon_steelhead/united_states_v_oregon_DEIS.html|website=www.westcoast.fisheries.noaa.gov|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=en-us}}</ref> This management agreement looks to gather information on fish harvesting through means including gillnets.<ref>{{cite web|title=2008-2017 United States v. Oregon Management Agreement May 2008|url=https://www.fws.gov/pacific/fisheries/hatcheryreview/Reports/snakeriver/SR--079.revised.2008-17USvOR_Mngmt_Agrmt.pdf|website=U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref> The parties involved will convene again to decide on further action after the current agreement ends.\n\nThe gill-netting season in Minnesota can vary from county to county and the net types used are regulated on a lake by lake basis by the Minnesota Department of Natural Resources.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://files.dnr.state.mn.us/rlp/regulations/fishing/whitefish-tullibee.pdf|title=Minnesota Gill Netting Regualtions|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nVirginia's gill-netting season is regulated by the Virginia Marine Resources Commission. During different months of the year, certain rivers have restricted mesh sizes, which vary by location.<ref>{{cite web|title=CHAPTER: PERTAINING TO THE SETTING AND MESH SIZE OF GILL NETS|url=http://www.mrc.state.va.us/regulations/FR751.shtm|website=www.mrc.state.va.us|publisher=Virginia Marine Resources Commission|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThere have been proposed regulations to shut down drift gill net fisheries whose by-catch numbers (which include dolphins, sea turtles and other marine life) were too high. In 2014, California lawmakers pushed for the banning of gillnet fishing through letters to federal fishing companies.<ref>{{cite web|title=California Lawmakers Call for End to the Use of Drift Gillnets off the West Coast|url=http://oceana.org/news-media/press-center/press-releases/california-lawmakers-call-for-end-to-the-use-of-drift-gillnets-off-the-west-coast|website=Oceana|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=en}}</ref> The progress for these regulations have been paused in California mid 2017.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://seaturtles.org/drift-gillnets-in-california/|title=Drift Gillnets in California|last=|first=|date=2017|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the High Seas Fishing Compliance Act from 1996, a permit is require for all commercial fishing vessels that are registered in the United States and under this act, vessels must have a record of all their fishing efforts on the high seas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.westcoast.fisheries.noaa.gov/fisheries/management/high_seas_fishing_compliance.html|title=NOAA Fisheries- West Coast Region|last=|first=|date=2017|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAs of November 2017, there has been a bill introduced to improve the management of [[Drift netting|driftnets]], with gillnets being under the umbrella of this fishing tool.<ref name=\":0\">https://www.pcouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/G1_Sup_Att14_Draft_S.Bill_Driftnet_Fishing_NOV2017BB.pdf</ref>  The bill's focus is to ban the use of large-scale nets while supporting the use of alternative methods of fishing to decrease the maximum amount of [[bycatch]]. There is also a compensation plan proposed in the bill for fishery participants who stop using large-scale nets.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Selectivity==\n[[Image:Gillnet selectivity.png|thumb|300px|Selectivity properties of a gillnet on a hypothetical population]]\n\nGillnets are a series of panels of meshes with a weighted \"foot rope\" along the bottom, and a ''headline'', to which floats are attached. By altering the ratio of floats to weights, buoyancy changes,<ref>Martin 1994, pp. 52-57.</ref> and the net can therefore be set to fish at any depth in the water column. In commercial fisheries, the meshes of a gillnet are uniform in size and shape. Fish smaller than the mesh of the net pass through unhindered, while those too large to push their heads through the meshes as far as their gills are not retained. This gives gillnets the ability to target a specific size of fish, unlike other net gears such as [[trawling|trawls]], in which smaller fish pass through the meshes and all larger fish are captured in the net{{ref|Pawson}}.\n\n===Salmon===\nCommercial gillnet fisheries are still an important method of harvesting [[salmon]] in Alaska, British Columbia, Washington, and Oregon. In the lower [[Columbia River]], non-Indian commercial salmon fisheries for spring Chinook have developed methods of selectively harvesting adipose fin clipped hatchery salmon using small mesh gillnets known as [[tangle net]]s or tooth nets.  Non-adipose fin clipped fish (primarily natural origin salmon) must be released.<ref>http://wdfw.wa.gov/publications/01353/wdfw01353.pdf</ref> Fishery management agencies estimate a relatively low release [[Fish mortality|mortality rate]] on salmon and [[Rainbow trout|steelhead]] released from these small mesh gillnets.\n\nProblems that can arise from selective harvesting are smaller reproducing adult fish, as well as the unexpected mortality of the fish which sustain injuries from the gillnet but are not retained in the fishery. Most salmon populations include several [[Age class structure|age classes]], allowing for fish of different ages, and sizes, to reproduce with each other. A recent 2009 study looked at 59 years of catch and escapement data of [[Bristol Bay]] [[sockeye salmon]] to determine age and size at maturity trends attributable to the selectivity of commercial gillnet harvests. The study found that the larger females (>550&nbsp;mm) of all age classes were most susceptible to harvest.<ref name=\"Kendall, Neala W 2009\">Kendall, Neala W, Jeffery J. Hard and Thomas P. Quinn. 2009. Quantifying Six Decades of Fishery Selection for Size and Age at Maturity in Sockeye Salmon. Evolutionary Applications. 523-536.</ref> The study suggests that smaller, younger fish were more likely to successfully traverse the gillnet fishery and reproduce than the larger fish. The study also found that the average length of sockeye harvested from 1946\u20132005 was 8&nbsp;mm larger than the sockeye who escaped the gillnet fishery to spawn, reducing the fecundity of the average female by 5%, or 104 eggs.<ref name=\"Kendall, Neala W 2009\"/> If a salmon enters a gillnet, but manages to escape, it can sustain injuries. These injuries can lead to a lower degree of reproductive success. A study aimed at quantifying mortality of Bristol Bay sockeye salmon due to gillnet-related injuries found that 11\u201329% of sockeye sustained fishery-related injuries attributable to gillnets, and 51% of those fish were expected to not reproduce.<ref>Baker, Matthew R and Daniel E Schindler. 2009. Unaccounted Mortality in Salmon Fisheries:  Non-retention in Gillnets and Effects on Estimates of Spawners. Journal of Applied Ecology (46). 752-761.</ref>\n\nGillnets are sometimes a controversial gear type especially among sport fishers who argue they are inappropriate especially for salmon fisheries. These arguments are often related to allocation issues between commercial and recreational (sport) fisheries and not conservation issues.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.opb.org/news/article/gillnet-ban-angers-fishers/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608063729/http://www.opb.org/news/article/gillnet-ban-angers-fishers/ |archive-date=2013-06-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Most salmon fisheries, especially those targeting Pacific salmon in North America, are strictly managed to minimize total impacts to specific populations and salmon fishery managers continue to allow the use of gillnets in these fisheries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcouncil.org/salmon/background/|title=Background  -  Pacific Fishery Management Council|author=|date=|website=www.pcouncil.org|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, University of Washington Fisheries Professor Emeritus Stephen Mathews compared Puget Sound bycatch data for the non-treaty gillnet and purse seine keta salmon fisheries. He found that although neither fishery had major bycatch problems with nontarget salmonids, the gillnet fishery has substantially less impact on nontarget Chinook salmon. His fulltext report is available from the Washington State [http://soundcatch.org Puget Sound Salmon Commission].\n\n===Swordfish===\nGillnets are also used out in the deep sea for fisheries whose primary catch is swordfish. California driftnet fisheries have some of the highest rates of by-catch with 12 percent of the catch being the targeted swordfish while up to 68 percent of the catch being by-catch that will be tossed back to sea.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n===Alternatives===\nGiven the selective properties of gillnet fishing, alternative methods of harvest are currently being studied. Recent WDF&W reports suggest that purse seine is the most productive method with having highest [[catch per unit effort]] (CPUE), but has little information on the effectiveness of selectively harvesting hatchery-reared salmon.<ref>WDF&W. 2010. 2010 Alternative Gear Catch...</ref> More conclusive research has been conducted jointly between the Confederated Tribes of the Colville Reservation and Bonneville Power Administration on a 10-year study on selective harvest methods of hatchery origin salmon in the Upper Columbia River by purse seine and tangle net. Their 2009 and 2010 findings show that purse seines have a higher percentage of survivability and higher CPUE than does tangle nets.<ref>Colville Tribe. 2011. Major Results...</ref> A Colville Tribe biologist reports that during these two years the tribe harvested 3,163 hatchery Chinook while releasing 2,346 wild Chinook with only 1.4% direct or immediate mortality using purse seines,<ref>Rayton, Michael. 2010. Declaration of Support...</ref> whereas the tangle net was far less productive but had an approximate 12.5% mortality. Researchers commented that the use of recovery boxes and shortened periods between checking the nets would have likely decreased mortality rates. While there is data that shows success of selective methods of harvest at protecting wild and ESA listed salmon, there still must be social acceptance of new methods of fishing.\n\nThere have also been studies done to see differing strategies that could potentially decrease avian by-catch in coastal fisheries. These include three strategies that have a possible reduction in up to 75% of avian by-catch: gear modifications, where visual devices will be placed near the top of the net so birds will be able to see the nets; abundance-based fishery openings, where of birds will determine whether the nets will be set out or not; and time-of-day restrictions, which goes along with abundance- where bird by catch tended to occur at dawn and dusk, where as fish catch occurred mostly at dawn.<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Novel Tools to Reduce Seabird Bycatch in Coastal Gillnet Fisheries|last=Melvin|first=Edward F.|date=December 1999|doi=10.1046/j.1523-1739.1999.98426.x|volume=13|issue = 6|journal=Conservation Biology|pages=1386\u20131397}}</ref>\n\nFor marine mammal by-catch, field experiments have shown that the use of pingers on nets resulted in significantly lower numbers of by-catch than nets without pingers. After this study was completed by Jay Barlow, it was determined that there would be a 12-fold decrease in [[short-beaked common dolphin]]s caught, a 4-fold decrease in other [[cetacea]]ns and a 3-fold decrease in [[pinniped]]s for nets containing pingers.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Barlow|first=Jay|date=April 2003|title=FIELD EXPERIMENTS SHOW THAT ACOUSTIC PINGERS REDUCE MARINE MAMMAL BYCATCH IN THE CALIFORNIA DRIFT GILL NET FISHERY|journal=Marine Mammal Science|volume=19|issue=2|pages=265\u2013283|doi=10.1111/j.1748-7692.2003.tb01108.x|url=http://digitalcommons.unl.edu/usdeptcommercepub/236}}</ref>\n\n==Types of gillnets==\nThe [[FAO]] classifies gillnet gear types as follows:\n\n===Set gillnets===\nSet gillnets consist of a single netting wall kept vertical by a floatline (upper line/headrope) and a weighted groundline (lower line/footrope). Small [[Fishing float|floats]], usually shaped like eggs or cylinders and made of solid plastic, are evenly distributed along the floatline, while [[Fishing sinker|lead weights]] are evenly distributed along groundline. The lower line can also be made of lead cored rope, which does not need additional weight. The net is set on the bottom, or at a distance above it and held in place with anchors or weights on both ends. By adjusting the design these nets can fish in surface layers, in mid water or at the bottom, targeting [[pelagic]], [[demersal]] or [[benthic]] species. On small boats gillnets are handled by hand. Larger boats use hydraulic net haulers or net drums. Set gillnets are widely used all over the world, and are employed both in inland and sea waters. They are popular with [[Artisan fishing|artisanal fisheries]] because no specialized gear is needed, and it is low cost based on the relationship of fuel/fish.<ref name=\"gillnet\">[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Gillnets]</ref>\n\n===Encircling gillnets===\nEncircling gillnets are gillnets set vertically in shallow water, with the floatline remaining at the surface so they encircle fish. Small open boats or canoes can be used to set the net around the fish. Once the fish are encircled, the fishers shout and splash the water to panic the fish so they gill or entangle themselves. There is little negative impact on the environment.<ref name=\"FAO:Gillnets\" /> As soon as the gear is set the scaring takes place and the net is hauled back in. The fish are alive and [[discards]] can be returned to the sea. Encircling gillnets are commonly used by groups of small-scale fishers, and does not require other equipment.<ref name=\"FAO:Gillnets\">[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/221/en Gillnets]</ref>\n\n[[File:Drawing of a gill netter.png|thumb|A gill netter]]\n\n===Combined gillnets-trammel nets===\nThis bottom-set gear has two parts:\n* the upper part is a standard gillnet where semi-[[Demersal fish|demersal]] or [[pelagic fish]] can be gilled\n* the lower part is a trammel net where bottom fish can entangle.\n\nThe combined nets are maintained more or less vertically in the usual way by floats on the floatline and weights on the groundline. They are set on the bottom. After a time depending on the target species, they are hauled on board. Traditional combined nets were hauled by hand, especially on smaller boats. Recent hydraulic driven net haulers are now common. The gilled, entangled and enmeshed fish are removed from the net by hand. Of some concern with this method is [[ghost fishing]] by lost nets and [[bycatch]] of diving seabirds. Nets combined in this way were first used in the Mediterranean.<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/252/en Combined gillnets-trammel nets]</ref>\n\n===Drift nets===\n{{main|Drift net}}\nA '''drift net''' consists of one or more panels of webbing fastened together. They are left free to drift with the current, usually near the surface or not far below it. Floats on the floatline and weights on the groundline keep them vertical. Drift nets drift with the current while they are connected with the operating vessel, the driftnetter or [[Drifter (fishing boat)|drifter]].\n\nDrift nets are usually used to catch [[Shoaling and schooling|schooling]] [[forage fish]] such as [[herring]] and [[sardine]]s, and also larger [[pelagic fish]] such as [[tuna]], [[salmon]] and pelagic [[squid]]. Net haulers are usually used to set and haul driftnets, with a drifter capstan on the forepart of the vessel. In developing countries most nets are hauled by hand. The mesh size of the gillnets is very effective at selecting or regulating the size of fish caught. The drift net has a low fuel/fish energy consumption compared to other fishing gear. However, the issue of concern with this type of net is the [[bycatch]] of species that are not targeted, such as marine mammals, seabirds and to a minor extent turtles. The use of drift nets longer than 2.5 kilometres on the [[high seas]] was banned by the United Nations in 1991. Prior to this ban, drift nets were reaching lengths of 60 kilometres. However, there are still serious concerns with ongoing violations.<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/220/en Driftnets]</ref>\n\n===Gillnets and entangling nets===\nThe tangle net, or tooth net, originated in British Columbia, Canada, as a gear specifically developed for selective fisheries.<ref>Petrunia, William Mark (1997). \"Tooth Net Fishery. Report on Scientific License 96.149.\" Jan. 5, 1997.</ref> Tangle nets have smaller mesh sizes than standard gillnets. They are designed to catch fish by their nose or jaw, enabling bycatch to be resuscitated and released unharmed. Tangle nets as adapted to the mark-selective fishery for spring Chinook salmon on the lower Columbia River have a standard mesh size of 4-1/4&nbsp;inches (10.8&nbsp;cm.). Short net lengths and soak times are used in an effort to land fish in good condition. Tangle nets are typically used in situations where the release of certain (usually wild) fish unharmed is desirable. In a typical situation calling for the use of a tangle net, for instance, all fish retaining their adipose fins (usually wild) must be returned to the water. Tangle nets are used in conjunction with a live recovery box, which acts as a resuscitation chamber for unmarked fish that appear lethargic or stressed before their release into the water.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salmonforall.org/tanglenet/|title=Salmon For All   \u00bb A Sustainable Fishery|author=|date=|website=www.salmonforall.org|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref><ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Gillnets and entangling nets]</ref>\n<!--\n===Gillnets and entangling nets (not specified)===\n<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Gillnets and entangling nets (not specified)]</ref>\n\n===Fixed gillnets (on stakes)===\n<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Fixed gillnets (on stakes)]</ref>\n-->\n\n==Historical images==\n{{multiple image\n | align = center\n | direction = horizontal\n | header            = Salmon gillnetting\n | header_align      = center\n | image1    = Salmon gill net boat.jpg\n | width1    = 244\n | alt1      = \n | caption1  = <center>Salmon gill net boat with drum</center>\n | image2    = Repairing salmon gill net.jpg\n | width2    = 136\n | alt2      = \n | caption2  = <center>Repairing salmon gillnet</center>\n | image3    = Gill net hauled in over a power-driven drum.jpg\n | width3    = 285\n | alt3      = \n | caption3  = <center>Hauling the gill net over the power-driven drum</center>\n | image4    = Removing salmon from gillnet.jpg\n | width4    = 187\n | alt4      = \n | caption4  = <center>Removing salmon from the gillnet</center>\n}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n#{{note|Erzini}} Erzini, K. Monteiro, C., Ribeiro, J., Santos, M., Gaspar, M., Montiero, P. & Borges, T. (1997) An experimental study of \"ghost-fishing\" off the Algarve (southern Portugal). Marine Ecology Progress Series 158:257-265.\n#{{note|Hall}} Hall, M.A. (1998) An ecological view of the tuna-dolphin problem: impacts and trade-offs. Reviews in Fish Biology and Fisheries. 8:1-34.\n#{{note|Kaiser}} Kaiser, M.J, Bullimore, B., Newman, P., Lock, K. & Gilbert, S. (1996) Catches in \"ghost-fishing\" set nets. Marine Ecology Progress Series. 145:11-16.\n#{{note|Pawson}} Potter, E.C.E. & Pawson, M.G. (1991) Gill Netting. MAFF Fisheries Leaflet 69. [http://www.cefas.co.uk/Publications/lableaflets/lableaflet69.pdf]\n#{{note|Puente}} Puente, E. (1997) Incidental impacts of gill nets. Report to the European Commission, No. 94/095,152.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Gillnets}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060218081502/http://homepage.mac.com/mooncusser/iMovieTheater3.html Video: Gillnets in Operation]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c_6hV6rPDYU Video: Gillnetting the Copper River Delta, Alaska]\n* [http://www.salmonforall.org/tanglenet/ Video: Tangle Net Fishing on the Columbia River]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050217140841/http://www.fao.org/documents/show_cdr.asp?url_file=%2FDOCREP%2F005%2FX7788E%2FX7788E00.HTM Manual on estimation of selectivity for gillnet and longline gears in abundance surveys] - report for Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations, 2000.\n* http://www.seawatch.org/position_papers/gillnet.php\n* [http://soundcatch.org Puget Sound Salmon Commission (WSDAg) bycatch study]\n\n{{fishing tackle|expanded=techniques}}\n{{fisheries and fishing}}\n\n[[Category:Fishing equipment]]\n[[Category:Fishing techniques and methods]]\n[[Category:Fishing nets]]\n\n[[id:Jaring insang]]\n[[pl:Sie\u0107 skrzelowa]]\n[[fi:Kalaverkko]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Eilif Peterssen-Laksefiskeren (1889).jpg|thumb|300px|right|Oil painting of gillnetting, ''The salmon fisher'' by [[Eilif Peterssen]].]]\n\n'''Gillnetting''' is a common fishing method used by [[fishing industry|commercial]] and [[Artisanal fishing|artisanal]] fishers of all the oceans and in some freshwater and estuary areas. Gill nets are composed of vertical panels of netting that hang from a line with regularly spaced floaters that hold the line on the surface of the water. The floats are sometimes called \"corks\" and the line with corks is generally referred to as a \"cork line.\" The line along the bottom of the panels is generally weighted. Traditionally this line has been weighted with lead and may be referred to as  \"lead line.\"  A gill net is normally set in a straight line. Gill nets can be characterized by mesh size, as well as colour and type of filament from which they are made. Fish may be caught by gill nets in three ways:\n\n# Wedged&nbsp;\u2013 held by the mesh around the body.\n# Gilled&nbsp;\u2013 held by mesh slipping behind the [[operculum (fish)|opercula]].\n# Tangled&nbsp;\u2013 held by teeth, spines, [[maxilla|maxillaries]], or other protrusions without the body penetrating the mesh.\n\nMost often fish are gilled. A fish swims into a net and passes only part way through the mesh. When it struggles to free itself, the twine slips behind the gill cover and prevents escape.<ref>Murphy, B. and Willis, D. (1996) [http://www.afsbooks.org/x55029xm \"Fisheries Techniques: Second edition.\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221024307/http://afsbooks.org/x55029xm |date=2013-02-21 }} Bethesda, MD: American Fisheries Society.</ref>\n\nGillnets are so effective that their use is closely monitored and regulated by fisheries management and [[enforcement]] agencies. [[Mesh size]], twine strength, as well as net length and depth are all closely regulated to reduce [[bycatch]] of non-target species. Gillnets have a high degree of size selectivity. Most [[Salmon#Salmon fisheries|salmon fisheries]] in particular have an extremely low incidence of catching non-target species.<ref>[http://www.dfw.state.or.us/fish/OSCRP/CRM/docs/Selective_Fisheries_JN_071220.pdf Selective Fisheries] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224930/http://www.dfw.state.or.us/fish/OSCRP/CRM/docs/Selective_Fisheries_JN_071220.pdf |date=2016-03-03 }} ''Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife''. Retrieved 26 September 2014.</ref>\n[[File:BC Bow Picker Mahalo Kai (Commercial Salmon Gillnetter).jpg|alt=image of a commercial salmon bow picker, Mahalo Kai; drum holding net is located in the bow of the boat. The cabin is in the rear.|thumb|Contemporary Canadian commercial salmon bowpicker on trailer.  Gillnet is evident on the metal drum in the bow of the boat. ]]\nA fishing vessel rigged to fish by gillnetting is a '''gillnetter'''. A gillnetter which deploys its gillnet from the [[Bow (ship)|bow]] is a '''[[:File:BC Bow Picker Mahalo Kai (Commercial Salmon Gillnetter).jpg|bowpicker]]''', while one which deploys its gillnet from the [[stern]] is a '''sternpicker'''.\n\n==History==\n{{see also|History of fishing}}\n[[File:Fish and Wildlife Service worker on boat checking gill net full of fish.jpg|thumb|[[Fish and Wildlife Service]] worker on boat checking gillnet full of fish.]]\n\nGillnets existed in ancient times, as archaeological evidence from the Middle East demonstrates.<ref>Nun, Mendel (1989). ''The Sea of Galilee and Its Fishermen in the New Testament,'' pp. 28-44. Kibbutz Ein Gev, Kinnereth Sailing Co.</ref> In North America, Native American fishermen used cedar canoes and natural fibre nets, e.g., made with nettles or the inner bark of cedar.<ref>Stewart, Hilary (1977). ''Indian Fishing: Early Methods on the Northwest Coast,'' p.79 in 1st paperback edition, 1982. Seattle, University of Washington Press.</ref> They would attach stones to the bottom of the nets as weights, and pieces of wood to the top, to use as floats. This allowed the net to suspend straight up and down in the water. Each net would be suspended either from shore or between two boats. Native fishers in the Pacific Northwest, Canada, and Alaska still commonly use gillnets in their fisheries for [[salmon]] and [[Rainbow trout|steelhead]].\n\nBoth drift gillnets and setnets have long been used by cultures around the world. There is evidence of fisheries exploitation, including gillnetting, going far back in Japanese history, with many specific details available from the [[Edo period]] (1603\u20131868).<ref>Ruddle, Kenneth and Akimich, Tomoya. \"Sea Tenure in Japan and the Southwestern Ryukyus,\" in Cordell, John, Ed. (1989), ''A Sea of Small Boats'', pp. 337-370. Cambridge, Mass., Cultural Survival, Inc.</ref> Fisheries in the [[Shetland]] Islands, which were settled by [[Norsemen]] during the [[Viking age]], share cultural and technological similarities with Norwegian fisheries, including gillnet fisheries for herring.<ref>Goodlad, C.A. (1970). ''Shetland Fishing Saga'', pp. 59-60. The Shetland Times, Ltd.</ref> Many of the Norwegian immigrant fishermen who came to fish in the great Columbia River salmon fishery during the second half of the 19th century did so because they had experience in the gillnet fishery for cod in the waters surrounding the [[Lofoten]] Islands of northern [[Norway]].<ref>Martin, Irene (1994). ''Legacy and Testament: The Story of the Columbia River Gillnetter'', p. 38. Pullman, Washington State University Press.</ref> Gillnets were used as part of the seasonal round by [[Sweden|Swedish]] fishermen as well.<ref>Lofgen, Ovar. \"Marine Ecotypes in Preindustrial Sweden: A Comparative Discussion of Swedish Peasant Fishermen,\" in Andersen, Raoul, Ed. (1979), ''North Atlantic Maritime Cultures'', pp. 83-109. The Hague, Mouton.</ref> Welsh and English fishermen gillnetted for Atlantic salmon in the rivers of [[Wales]] and [[England]] in [[coracle]]s, using hand-made nets, for at least several centuries.<ref>Jenkins, J. Geraint (1974). ''Nets and Coracles'', p. 68. London, David and Charles.</ref> These are but a few of the examples of historic gillnet fisheries around the world.\n\nGillnetting was an early fishing technology in colonial America,{{vague|reason=\"Colonial America\" is not a [[proper name]] of any region. (But \"colonial America\" is ambiguous among (at least) the New World, the 13 Colonies, and North America north of the [[Rio Grande]]|date=February 2018}} used for example, in fisheries for Atlantic salmon and shad.<ref>Netboy, Anthony (1973) ''The Salmon: Their Fight for Survival,'' pp. 181-182. Boston, Houghton Mifflin.</ref> Immigrant fishermen from northern Europe and the Mediterranean brought a number of different adaptations of the technology from their respective homelands with them to the rapidly expanding salmon fisheries of the Columbia River from the 1860s onward.<ref>Martin, 1994, p. 44.</ref> The boats used by these fisherman were typically around {{convert|25|ft|m|0}} long and powered by oars. Many of these boats also had small sails and were called \"row-sail\" boats. At the beginning of the 1900s, steam powered ships would haul these smaller boats to their fishing grounds and retrieve them at the end of each day. However, at that time [[gasoline|gas]] powered boats were beginning to make their appearance, and by the 1930s, the row-sail boat had virtually disappeared, except in Bristol Bay, Alaska, where motors were prohibited in the gillnet fishery by territorial law until 1951.<ref>Andrews, Ralph W. and Larsen, A.K. (1959). ''Fish and Ships'', p. 108. Seattle, Superior Publishing Co.</ref>\n[[File:MENDING A GILLNET ON THE DOCK AT ST. HELENS ON THE COLUMBIA RIVER - NARA - 548102.jpg|right|thumb|A fisherman repairs a gillnet (April 1973, [[St. Helens, Oregon]])]]\n\nIn 1931, the first powered drum was created by Laurie Jarelainen.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}} The drum is a circular device that is set to the side of the boat and draws in the nets. The powered drum allowed the nets to be drawn in much faster and along with the faster gas powered boats, fisherman were able to fish in areas they had previously been unable to go into, thereby revolutionizing the fishing industry.\n\nDuring World War II, navigation and communication devices, as well as many other forms of maritime equipment (ex. depth-sounding and radar) were improved and made more compact. These devices became much more accessible to the average fisherman, thus making their range and mobility increasingly larger. It also served to make the industry much more competitive, as the fisherman were forced to invest more in boats and equipment to stay current with developing technology.\n\nThe introduction of fine [[synthetic fibre]]s such as [[nylon]] in the construction of fishing gear during the 1960s marked an expansion in the commercial use of gillnets. The new materials were cheaper and easier to handle, lasted longer and required less maintenance than natural fibres. In addition, [[Multifilament fishing line|multifilament nylon]], [[Monofilament fishing line|monofilament]] or [[Braided fishing line|multimonofilament fibres]] become almost invisible in water, so nets made with synthetic twines generally caught greater numbers of fish than natural fibre nets used in comparable situations.\n\nNylon is highly resistant to abrasion and degradation, hence the netting has the potential to last for many years if it is not recovered. This [[ghost fishing]] is of environmental concern. Attaching the gillnet floats with biodegradable material can reduce the problem.<ref name=\"gillnet\"/> However it is difficult to generalize about the longevity of ghost-fishing gillnets due to the varying environments in which they are used. Some researchers have found gill-nets still catching fish and crustaceans over a year after loss{{ref|Kaiser}}, while others have found lost nets destroyed by wave action within one month{{ref|Puente}} or overgrown with [[seaweed]]s, increasing their visibility and reducing their catching potential to such an extent that they became a microhabitat used by small fish.{{ref|Erzini}}\n\nThis type of net was heavily used by many [[Japan]]ese, [[South Korea]]n, and [[Taiwan]]ese fishing fleets on the high seas in the 1980s to target [[tuna]]s. Although highly selective with respect to size class of animals captured, gillnets are associated with high numbers of incidental captures of [[cetacea]]ns ([[whale]]s and [[dolphin]]s). In the Sri Lankan gillnet fishery, one dolphin is caught for every 1.7\u20134.0 tonnes of tuna landed{{ref|Hall}}. This compares poorly with the rate of one dolphin per 70 tonnes of tuna landed in the eastern Pacific [[purse seine]] tuna fishery.\n\nGillnets are sometimes used by [[Fisheries science|fisheries scientists]] to monitor fish populations.<ref>Bruce Crawford. \"Variable Mesh Gill Nets (in Lakes).\" In Johnson, David, et al. ''Salmonid Field Protocols Handbook''. Bethesda, Maryland, American Fisheries Society, 2007, pp. 425-433.</ref>\n\n==Legal status==\n[[United Nations General Assembly]] Resolution 46/215<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/documents/ga/res/46/a46r215|title=A/RES/46/215.  Large-scale pelagic drift-net fishing and its impact on the living marine resources of the world's oceans and seas|author=|date=|website=www.un.org|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref> called for the cessation of all \"large-scale pelagic drift-net fishing\" in [[international waters]] by the end of 1992.  The laws of individual countries vary with regard to fishing in waters under their jurisdiction.\n\nPossession of gillnets is illegal in some U.S. states and heavily regulated in others.\n\nOregon voters had the chance to decide on whether gillnetting will continue in the [[Columbia River]] in November 2012 by voting on Measure 81.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yes on Measure 81 Stop Gillnetting|url=http://www.stopgillnetting.com/|accessdate=14 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120814002555/http://www.stopgillnetting.com/|archive-date=14 August 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The measure was defeated with 65% of Oregon voters voting against the measure and allowing commercial gillnet fishing to continue on the Columbia River.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sos.oregon.gov/elections/Documents/results/results-11-2012.pdf|title=Oregon Secretary of State: Official Results November 2012 General Election|author=|date=|website=sos.oregon.gov|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Columbia River Basin is currently under a management agreement that spans from 2008 to December 31, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=NOAA Fisheries West Coast Region|title=Environmental Impact Statement for Programmatic Review of Harvest Actions for Salmon and Steelhead in the Columbia Basin related to U.S. v. Oregon :: NOAA Fisheries West Coast Region |url=http://www.westcoast.fisheries.noaa.gov/fisheries/salmon_steelhead/united_states_v_oregon_DEIS.html|website=www.westcoast.fisheries.noaa.gov|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=en-us}}</ref> This management agreement looks to gather information on fish harvesting through means including gillnets.<ref>{{cite web|title=2008-2017 United States v. Oregon Management Agreement May 2008|url=https://www.fws.gov/pacific/fisheries/hatcheryreview/Reports/snakeriver/SR--079.revised.2008-17USvOR_Mngmt_Agrmt.pdf|website=U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref> The parties involved will convene again to decide on further action after the current agreement ends.\n\nThe gill-netting season in Minnesota can vary from county to county and the net types used are regulated on a lake by lake basis by the Minnesota Department of Natural Resources.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://files.dnr.state.mn.us/rlp/regulations/fishing/whitefish-tullibee.pdf|title=Minnesota Gill Netting Regualtions|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nVirginia's gill-netting season is regulated by the Virginia Marine Resources Commission. During different months of the year, certain rivers have restricted mesh sizes, which vary by location.<ref>{{cite web|title=CHAPTER: PERTAINING TO THE SETTING AND MESH SIZE OF GILL NETS|url=http://www.mrc.state.va.us/regulations/FR751.shtm|website=www.mrc.state.va.us|publisher=Virginia Marine Resources Commission|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThere have been proposed regulations to shut down drift gill net fisheries whose by-catch numbers (which include dolphins, sea turtles and other marine life) were too high. In 2014, California lawmakers pushed for the banning of gillnet fishing through letters to federal fishing companies.<ref>{{cite web|title=California Lawmakers Call for End to the Use of Drift Gillnets off the West Coast|url=http://oceana.org/news-media/press-center/press-releases/california-lawmakers-call-for-end-to-the-use-of-drift-gillnets-off-the-west-coast|website=Oceana|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=en}}</ref> The progress for these regulations have been paused in California mid 2017.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://seaturtles.org/drift-gillnets-in-california/|title=Drift Gillnets in California|last=|first=|date=2017|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the High Seas Fishing Compliance Act from 1996, a permit is require for all commercial fishing vessels that are registered in the United States and under this act, vessels must have a record of all their fishing efforts on the high seas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.westcoast.fisheries.noaa.gov/fisheries/management/high_seas_fishing_compliance.html|title=NOAA Fisheries- West Coast Region|last=|first=|date=2017|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAs of November 2017, there has been a bill introduced to improve the management of [[Drift netting|driftnets]], with gillnets being under the umbrella of this fishing tool.<ref name=\":0\">https://www.pcouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/G1_Sup_Att14_Draft_S.Bill_Driftnet_Fishing_NOV2017BB.pdf</ref>  The bill's focus is to ban the use of large-scale nets while supporting the use of alternative methods of fishing to decrease the maximum amount of [[bycatch]]. There is also a compensation plan proposed in the bill for fishery participants who stop using large-scale nets.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Selectivity==\n[[Image:Gillnet selectivity.png|thumb|300px|Selectivity properties of a gillnet on a hypothetical population]]\n\nGillnets are a series of panels of meshes with a weighted \"foot rope\" along the bottom, and a ''headline'', to which floats are attached. By altering the ratio of floats to weights, buoyancy changes,<ref>Martin 1994, pp. 52-57.</ref> and the net can therefore be set to fish at any depth in the water column. In commercial fisheries, the meshes of a gillnet are uniform in size and shape. Fish smaller than the mesh of the net pass through unhindered, while those too large to push their heads through the meshes as far as their gills are not retained. This gives gillnets the ability to target a specific size of fish, unlike other net gears such as [[trawling|trawls]], in which smaller fish pass through the meshes and all larger fish are captured in the net{{ref|Pawson}}.\n\n===Salmon===\nCommercial gillnet fisheries are still an important method of harvesting [[salmon]] in Alaska, British Columbia, Washington, and Oregon. In the lower [[Columbia River]], non-Indian commercial salmon fisheries for spring Chinook have developed methods of selectively harvesting adipose fin clipped hatchery salmon using small mesh gillnets known as [[tangle net]]s or tooth nets.  Non-adipose fin clipped fish (primarily natural origin salmon) must be released.<ref>http://wdfw.wa.gov/publications/01353/wdfw01353.pdf</ref> Fishery management agencies estimate a relatively low release [[Fish mortality|mortality rate]] on salmon and [[Rainbow trout|steelhead]] released from these small mesh gillnets.\n\nProblems that can arise from selective harvesting are smaller reproducing adult fish, as well as the unexpected mortality of the fish which sustain injuries from the gillnet but are not retained in the fishery. Most salmon populations include several [[Age class structure|age classes]], allowing for fish of different ages, and sizes, to reproduce with each other. A recent 2009 study looked at 59 years of catch and escapement data of [[Bristol Bay]] [[sockeye salmon]] to determine age and size at maturity trends attributable to the selectivity of commercial gillnet harvests. The study found that the larger females (>550&nbsp;mm) of all age classes were most susceptible to harvest.<ref name=\"Kendall, Neala W 2009\">Kendall, Neala W, Jeffery J. Hard and Thomas P. Quinn. 2009. Quantifying Six Decades of Fishery Selection for Size and Age at Maturity in Sockeye Salmon. Evolutionary Applications. 523-536.</ref> The study suggests that smaller, younger fish were more likely to successfully traverse the gillnet fishery and reproduce than the larger fish. The study also found that the average length of sockeye harvested from 1946\u20132005 was 8&nbsp;mm larger than the sockeye who escaped the gillnet fishery to spawn, reducing the fecundity of the average female by 5%, or 104 eggs.<ref name=\"Kendall, Neala W 2009\"/> If a salmon enters a gillnet, but manages to escape, it can sustain injuries. These injuries can lead to a lower degree of reproductive success. A study aimed at quantifying mortality of Bristol Bay sockeye salmon due to gillnet-related injuries found that 11\u201329% of sockeye sustained fishery-related injuries attributable to gillnets, and 51% of those fish were expected to not reproduce.<ref>Baker, Matthew R and Daniel E Schindler. 2009. Unaccounted Mortality in Salmon Fisheries:  Non-retention in Gillnets and Effects on Estimates of Spawners. Journal of Applied Ecology (46). 752-761.</ref>\n\nGillnets are sometimes a controversial gear type especially among sport fishers who argue they are inappropriate especially for salmon fisheries. These arguments are often related to allocation issues between commercial and recreational (sport) fisheries and not conservation issues.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.opb.org/news/article/gillnet-ban-angers-fishers/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608063729/http://www.opb.org/news/article/gillnet-ban-angers-fishers/ |archive-date=2013-06-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Most salmon fisheries, especially those targeting Pacific salmon in North America, are strictly managed to minimize total impacts to specific populations and salmon fishery managers continue to allow the use of gillnets in these fisheries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcouncil.org/salmon/background/|title=Background  -  Pacific Fishery Management Council|author=|date=|website=www.pcouncil.org|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, University of Washington Fisheries Professor Emeritus Stephen Mathews compared Puget Sound bycatch data for the non-treaty gillnet and purse seine keta salmon fisheries. He found that although neither fishery had major bycatch problems with nontarget salmonids, the gillnet fishery has substantially less impact on nontarget Chinook salmon. His fulltext report is available from the Washington State [http://soundcatch.org Puget Sound Salmon Commission].\n\n===Swordfish===\nGillnets are also used out in the deep sea for fisheries whose primary catch is swordfish. California driftnet fisheries have some of the highest rates of by-catch with 12 percent of the catch being the targeted swordfish while up to 68 percent of the catch being by-catch that will be tossed back to sea.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n===Alternatives===\nGiven the selective properties of gillnet fishing, alternative methods of harvest are currently being studied. Recent WDF&W reports suggest that purse seine is the most productive method with having highest [[catch per unit effort]] (CPUE), but has little information on the effectiveness of selectively harvesting hatchery-reared salmon.<ref>WDF&W. 2010. 2010 Alternative Gear Catch...</ref> More conclusive research has been conducted jointly between the Confederated Tribes of the Colville Reservation and Bonneville Power Administration on a 10-year study on selective harvest methods of hatchery origin salmon in the Upper Columbia River by purse seine and tangle net. Their 2009 and 2010 findings show that purse seines have a higher percentage of survivability and higher CPUE than does tangle nets.<ref>Colville Tribe. 2011. Major Results...</ref> A Colville Tribe biologist reports that during these two years the tribe harvested 3,163 hatchery Chinook while releasing 2,346 wild Chinook with only 1.4% direct or immediate mortality using purse seines,<ref>Rayton, Michael. 2010. Declaration of Support...</ref> whereas the tangle net was far less productive but had an approximate 12.5% mortality. Researchers commented that the use of recovery boxes and shortened periods between checking the nets would have likely decreased mortality rates. While there is data that shows success of selective methods of harvest at protecting wild and ESA listed salmon, there still must be social acceptance of new methods of fishing.\n\nThere have also been studies done to see differing strategies that could potentially decrease avian by-catch in coastal fisheries. These include three strategies that have a possible reduction in up to 75% of avian by-catch: gear modifications, where visual devices will be placed near the top of the net so birds will be able to see the nets; abundance-based fishery openings, where of birds will determine whether the nets will be set out or not; and time-of-day restrictions, which goes along with abundance- where bird by catch tended to occur at dawn and dusk, where as fish catch occurred mostly at dawn.<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Novel Tools to Reduce Seabird Bycatch in Coastal Gillnet Fisheries|last=Melvin|first=Edward F.|date=December 1999|doi=10.1046/j.1523-1739.1999.98426.x|volume=13|issue = 6|journal=Conservation Biology|pages=1386\u20131397}}</ref>\n\nFor marine mammal by-catch, field experiments have shown that the use of pingers on nets resulted in significantly lower numbers of by-catch than nets without pingers. After this study was completed by Jay Barlow, it was determined that there would be a 12-fold decrease in [[short-beaked common dolphin]]s caught, a 4-fold decrease in other [[cetacea]]ns and a 3-fold decrease in [[pinniped]]s for nets containing pingers.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Barlow|first=Jay|date=April 2003|title=FIELD EXPERIMENTS SHOW THAT ACOUSTIC PINGERS REDUCE MARINE MAMMAL BYCATCH IN THE CALIFORNIA DRIFT GILL NET FISHERY|journal=Marine Mammal Science|volume=19|issue=2|pages=265\u2013283|doi=10.1111/j.1748-7692.2003.tb01108.x|url=http://digitalcommons.unl.edu/usdeptcommercepub/236}}</ref>\n\n==Types of gillnets==\nThe [[FAO]] classifies gillnet gear types as follows:\n\n===Set gillnets===\nSet gillnets consist of a single netting wall kept vertical by a floatline (upper line/headrope) and a weighted groundline (lower line/footrope). Small [[Fishing float|floats]], usually shaped like eggs or cylinders and made of solid plastic, are evenly distributed along the floatline, while [[Fishing sinker|lead weights]] are evenly distributed along groundline. The lower line can also be made of lead cored rope, which does not need additional weight. The net is set on the bottom, or at a distance above it and held in place with anchors or weights on both ends. By adjusting the design these nets can fish in surface layers, in mid water or at the bottom, targeting [[pelagic]], [[demersal]] or [[benthic]] species. On small boats gillnets are handled by hand. Larger boats use hydraulic net haulers or net drums. Set gillnets are widely used all over the world, and are employed both in inland and sea waters. They are popular with [[Artisan fishing|artisanal fisheries]] because no specialized gear is needed, and it is low cost based on the relationship of fuel/fish.<ref name=\"gillnet\">[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Gillnets]</ref>\n\n===Encircling gillnets===\nEncircling gillnets are gillnets set vertically in shallow water, with the floatline remaining at the surface so they encircle fish. Small open boats or canoes can be used to set the net around the fish. Once the fish are encircled, the fishers shout and splash the water to panic the fish so they gill or entangle themselves. There is little negative impact on the environment.<ref name=\"FAO:Gillnets\" /> As soon as the gear is set the scaring takes place and the net is hauled back in. The fish are alive and [[discards]] can be returned to the sea. Encircling gillnets are commonly used by groups of small-scale fishers, and does not require other equipment.<ref name=\"FAO:Gillnets\">[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/221/en Gillnets]</ref>\n\n[[File:Drawing of a gill netter.png|thumb|A gill netter]]\n\n===Combined gillnets-trammel nets===\nThis bottom-set gear has two parts:\n* the upper part is a standard gillnet where semi-[[Demersal fish|demersal]] or [[pelagic fish]] can be gilled\n* the lower part is a trammel net where bottom fish can entangle.\n\nThe combined nets are maintained more or less vertically in the usual way by floats on the floatline and weights on the groundline. They are set on the bottom. After a time depending on the target species, they are hauled on board. Traditional combined nets were hauled by hand, especially on smaller boats. Recent hydraulic driven net haulers are now common. The gilled, entangled and enmeshed fish are removed from the net by hand. Of some concern with this method is [[ghost fishing]] by lost nets and [[bycatch]] of diving seabirds. Nets combined in this way were first used in the Mediterranean.<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/252/en Combined gillnets-trammel nets]</ref>\n\n===Drift nets===\n{{main|Drift net}}\nA '''drift net''' consists of one or more panels of webbing fastened together. They are left free to drift with the current, usually near the surface or not far below it. Floats on the floatline and weights on the groundline keep them vertical. Drift nets drift with the current while they are connected with the operating vessel, the driftnetter or [[Drifter (fishing boat)|drifter]].\n\nDrift nets are usually used to catch [[Shoaling and schooling|schooling]] [[forage fish]] such as [[herring]] and [[sardine]]s, and also larger [[pelagic fish]] such as [[tuna]], [[salmon]] and pelagic [[squid]]. Net haulers are usually used to set and haul driftnets, with a drifter capstan on the forepart of the vessel. In developing countries most nets are hauled by hand. The mesh size of the gillnets is very effective at selecting or regulating the size of fish caught. The drift net has a low fuel/fish energy consumption compared to other fishing gear. However, the issue of concern with this type of net is the [[bycatch]] of species that are not targeted, such as marine mammals, seabirds and to a minor extent turtles. The use of drift nets longer than 2.5 kilometres on the [[high seas]] was banned by the United Nations in 1991. Prior to this ban, drift nets were reaching lengths of 60 kilometres. However, there are still serious concerns with ongoing violations.<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/220/en Driftnets]</ref>\n\n===Gillnets and entangling nets===\nThe tangle net, or tooth net, originated in British Columbia, Canada, as a gear specifically developed for selective fisheries.<ref>Petrunia, William Mark (1997). \"Tooth Net Fishery. Report on Scientific License 96.149.\" Jan. 5, 1997.</ref> Tangle nets have smaller mesh sizes than standard gillnets. They are designed to catch fish by their nose or jaw, enabling bycatch to be resuscitated and released unharmed. Tangle nets as adapted to the mark-selective fishery for spring Chinook salmon on the lower Columbia River have a standard mesh size of 4-1/4&nbsp;inches (10.8&nbsp;cm.). Short net lengths and soak times are used in an effort to land fish in good condition. Tangle nets are typically used in situations where the release of certain (usually wild) fish unharmed is desirable. In a typical situation calling for the use of a tangle net, for instance, all fish retaining their adipose fins (usually wild) must be returned to the water. Tangle nets are used in conjunction with a live recovery box, which acts as a resuscitation chamber for unmarked fish that appear lethargic or stressed before their release into the water.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salmonforall.org/tanglenet/|title=Salmon For All   \u00bb A Sustainable Fishery|author=|date=|website=www.salmonforall.org|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref><ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Gillnets and entangling nets]</ref>\n<!--\n===Gillnets and entangling nets (not specified)===\n<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Gillnets and entangling nets (not specified)]</ref>\n\n===Fixed gillnets (on stakes)===\n<ref>[[FAO]]: Fishing Gear Types: [http://www.fao.org/fishery/geartype/219/en Fixed gillnets (on stakes)]</ref>\n-->\n\n==Historical images==\n{{multiple image\n | align = center\n | direction = horizontal\n | header            = Salmon gillnetting\n | header_align      = center\n | image1    = Salmon gill net boat.jpg\n | width1    = 244\n | alt1      = \n | caption1  = <center>Salmon gill net boat with drum</center>\n | image2    = Repairing salmon gill net.jpg\n | width2    = 136\n | alt2      = \n | caption2  = <center>Repairing salmon gillnet</center>\n | image3    = Gill net hauled in over a power-driven drum.jpg\n | width3    = 285\n | alt3      = \n | caption3  = <center>Hauling the gill net over the power-driven drum</center>\n | image4    = Removing salmon from gillnet.jpg\n | width4    = 187\n | alt4      = \n | caption4  = <center>Removing salmon from the gillnet</center>\n}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n#{{note|Erzini}} Erzini, K. Monteiro, C., Ribeiro, J., Santos, M., Gaspar, M., Montiero, P. & Borges, T. (1997) An experimental study of \"ghost-fishing\" off the Algarve (southern Portugal). Marine Ecology Progress Series 158:257-265.\n#{{note|Hall}} Hall, M.A. (1998) An ecological view of the tuna-dolphin problem: impacts and trade-offs. Reviews in Fish Biology and Fisheries. 8:1-34.\n#{{note|Kaiser}} Kaiser, M.J, Bullimore, B., Newman, P., Lock, K. & Gilbert, S. (1996) Catches in \"ghost-fishing\" set nets. Marine Ecology Progress Series. 145:11-16.\n#{{note|Pawson}} Potter, E.C.E. & Pawson, M.G. (1991) Gill Netting. MAFF Fisheries Leaflet 69. [http://www.cefas.co.uk/Publications/lableaflets/lableaflet69.pdf]\n#{{note|Puente}} Puente, E. (1997) Incidental impacts of gill nets. Report to the European Commission, No. 94/095,152.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Gillnets}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060218081502/http://homepage.mac.com/mooncusser/iMovieTheater3.html Video: Gillnets in Operation]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c_6hV6rPDYU Video: Gillnetting the Copper River Delta, Alaska]\n* [http://www.salmonforall.org/tanglenet/ Video: Tangle Net Fishing on the Columbia River]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050217140841/http://www.fao.org/documents/show_cdr.asp?url_file=%2FDOCREP%2F005%2FX7788E%2FX7788E00.HTM Manual on estimation of selectivity for gillnet and longline gears in abundance surveys] - report for Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations, 2000.\n* http://www.seawatch.org/position_papers/gillnet.php\n* [http://soundcatch.org Puget Sound Salmon Commission (WSDAg) bycatch study]\n\n{{fishing tackle|expanded=techniques}}\n{{fisheries and fishing}}\n\n[[Category:Fishing equipment]]\n[[Category:Fishing techniques and methods]]\n[[Category:Fishing nets]]\n\n[[id:Jaring insang]]\n[[pl:Sie\u0107 skrzelowa]]\n[[fi:Kalaverkko]]\n", "name_user": "Togue1971", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor text editing and one cite added.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gillnetting"}
{"title_page": "Paulo Dybala", "text_new": "{{short description|Argentine association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Paulo Dybala\n| image = 2017 FRIENDLY MATCH RUSSIA v ARGENTINA - Paulo Dybala 01.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Dybala with [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in 2017\n| fullname = Paulo Bruno Exequiel Dybala<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2015/dybala-sets-sights-on-silverware.php|title=Dybala sets sights on silverware. |publisher=Juventus FC|date=14 July 2015|accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|11|15|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia: List of players: Argentina |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=1 |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_place = Laguna Larga, [[C\u00f3rdoba Province, Argentina|C\u00f3rdoba]], Argentina\n| height = 1.77 m<ref name=profilo>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/it/squadre/prima-squadra/attaccanti/paulo-dybala/index.php|title=Paulo Dybala|publisher=juventus.com}}</ref>\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] / [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|Attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n| clubnumber = 10\n| youthyears1 = 2003\u20132011\n| youthclubs1 = [[Instituto Atl\u00e9tico Central C\u00f3rdoba|Instituto]]\n| years1 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs1 = [[Instituto Atl\u00e9tico Central C\u00f3rdoba|Instituto]]\n| caps1 = 38\n| goals1 = 17\n| years2 = 2012\u20132015\n| clubs2 = [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]]\n| caps2 = 89\n| goals2 = 21\n| years3 = 2015\u2013\n| clubs3 = [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n| caps3 = 152<!-- LEAGUE APPEARANCES AND GOALS ONLY !-->\n| goals3 = 64<!-- LEAGUE APPEARANCES AND GOALS ONLY !-->\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 29\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 18 November 2019\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{fb|ARG}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]}}\n{{Medal|3rd|[[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2019 Brazil]]|}}\n}}\n'''Paulo Bruno Exequiel Dybala''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8pawlo \u00f0i\u02c8\u03b2ala}};{{efn-ua|In isolation, ''Dybala'' is pronounced {{IPA-es|di\u02c8\u03b2ala|}}.}} {{lang-pl|Dyba\u0142a}}; born 15 November 1993) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Italian football updater|Juventus}} club [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]]. Considered Europe's top five leagues' 23rd most valuable player from a transfer value perspective [[International Centre for Sports Studies|CIES]],{{efn-ua|As of 12 June 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-observatory.com/IMG/sites/b5wp/2018/265/en/ |title=Most expensive big-5 league players: Salah behind Mbapp\u00e9 |publisher=International Centre for Sports Studies (CIES) |first1=Raffaele |last1=Poli |first2=Roger |last2=Besson |first3=Lo\u00efc |last3=Ravenel |date=13 June 2019 |accessdate=13 November 2019}}</ref>}} he is commonly referred to as \"''La Joya''\" (\"The Jewel\") due to his creative style of play, pace, talent, technique and eye for goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lmcordoba.com.ar/nota.php?ni=71388|title=Los maestros de la 'joya'|trans-title=The \"Jewel's\" teachers|publisher=La Ma\u00f1ana Cordoba|author1=Marcos Villalobo|language=Spanish|date=10 October 2011|accessdate=1 June 2015|archive-url=https://archive.is/20121230031329/http://www.lmcordoba.com.ar/nota.php?ni=71388|archive-date=30 December 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> Palermitans also refer to him as \"U Picciriddu\" (\u201cThe Kid,\" in the [[Sicilian language|Sicilian dialect]]), because of his young age when he signed for [[S.S.D. Palermo|Palermo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/juventus/2018/10/12-48555805/dybala_u_picciriddu_ecco_com_e_nato_il_soprannome/|title=Dybala \u00abu picciriddu\u00bb: ecco com'\u00e8 nato il soprannome|work=Tutto Sport|language=Italian|date=12 October 2018|access-date=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter beginning his career in Argentina with [[Instituto Atl\u00e9tico Central C\u00f3rdoba|Instituto de C\u00f3rdoba]] in 2011, Dybala moved to Italian club [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]] in 2012. He played three seasons for Palermo, two in [[Serie A]] and won [[Serie B]] in [[2013\u201314 Serie B|2013\u201314]]. In 2015, he joined Juventus for an initial fee of \u20ac32 million and has since made over 100 appearances for the club, winning the [[Double (association football)|double]] of Serie A and [[Coppa Italia]] in each of his three seasons. He has also been named in the [[Serie A Team of the Year]] three times.\n\nDybala made his senior international debut for Argentina in 2015 and was chosen for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] and the [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica]], helping his nation to win a bronze medal in the latter tournament.\n\n==Early life==\nDybala was born in Laguna Larga, [[C\u00f3rdoba Province, Argentina|C\u00f3rdoba]], [[Argentina]].<ref name=\"The Cordoba Connection\">{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/blog/espn-fc-united-blog/68/post/2948827/the-cordoba-connection-paulo-dybala-faces-franco-vazquez-luciano-vietto-in-champions-league|title=The Cordoba Connection: Dybala faces Vazquez, Vietto in Champions League|publisher=ESPN FC|author1=Nick Dorrington|date=13 September 2016|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref> His grandfather, Boles\u0142aw Dyba\u0142a, was from the village of [[Kra\u015bni\u00f3w]] in Poland; he fled from his country of birth to Argentina during [[World War II]].<ref name=\"Met\u00e0 polacco e met\u00e0 italiano\"/><ref name=\"dybala_newmessi\">{{cite news |url=http://sport.onet.pl/pilka-nozna/inne-ligi/paulo-dybala-nowy-messi-z-polskimi-korzeniami,1,5080257,wiadomosc.html |publisher=Sport.onet |language=Polish |title=Paulo Dybala \u2013 \"nowy Messi\" z polskimi korzeniami |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120405234500/http://sport.onet.pl/pilka-nozna/inne-ligi/paulo-dybala-nowy-messi-z-polskimi-korzeniami%2C1%2C5080257%2Cwiadomosc.html |archivedate=5 April 2012  }}</ref> Some of his grandfather's family moved to Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46867871|title=Paulo Dybala: How the Argentine 'Gladiator' went from rough diamond to Juventus 'jewel'|publisher=BBC Sport|author=Martin Mazur|date=17 January 2019|accessdate=18 January 2019}}</ref> Dybala's family also has Italian origins through his maternal great-grandmother, whose surname was Da Messa, from the [[Province of Naples]].<ref name=\"Met\u00e0 polacco e met\u00e0 italiano\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mediagol.it/palermo/dybala-meta-polacco-e-meta-italiano-spiego/ |title=DYBALA: \"Met\u00e0 polacco e met\u00e0 italiano, spiego\" |website=MediaGol.it |language=Italian |date=29 November 2014 |accessdate=12 January 2017 }}</ref><ref name=noitalian>{{cite news|url=https://www.football-italia.net/77547/dybala-%E2%80%98no-italian-feeling%E2%80%99 |publisher=Football Italia |language=English|title=Dybala\"No Italian feeling |date=24 December 2015 |accessdate=24 December 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"dybala_italian\">{{cite news |url=http://corrieredelmezzogiorno.corriere.it/napoli/notizie/sport/2012/12-luglio-2012/-scatta-raduno-rosanero-25-convocati-assente-giustificato-talento-dybala-201985057485.shtml |title=Scatta raduno rosanero: 25 convocati, assente giustificato Dybala |publisher=Il Corriere del Mezzogiorno |language=Italian |date=12 July 2012 |accessdate= 12 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportmediaset.mediaset.it/calcio/Nazionale/2014/articoli/1052202/nazionale-conte-vuole-dybala-in-azzurro.shtml|title=Nazionale, Conte vuole Dybala in azzurro|website=Sport Mediaset|language=Italian|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=2 October 2015}}</ref> Dybala obtained Italian citizenship on 13 August 2012.<ref name=\"Dybala \u00e8 cittadino italiano\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/esclusiva-tmw-palermo-dybala-e-cittadino-italiano-376629|title=ESCLUSIVA TMW - Palermo, Dybala \u00e8 cittadino italiano|publisher=TuttoMercatoWeb.com|language=Italian|author1=Alessio Alaimo|date=14 August 2012|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nDybala is the youngest of three brothers and lost his father in 2008 to cancer.\n\n==Club career==\n===Instituto de C\u00f3rdoba===\nNicknamed \"''La Joya''\"<ref name=\"dybala_lajoya\">{{cite news |url=http://www.ole.com.ar/instituto/Joya-bien_0_674932859.html |title=La Joya est\u00e1 bien |publisher=Ol\u00e8 |language=Spanish |date=2 April 2012 |accessdate=1 July 2012}}</ref> or \"''El pibe de la pensi\u00f3n''\",<ref name=\"dybala_elpibedelapension\">{{cite news |url=http://www.lmcordoba.com.ar/nota.php?ni=64071 |publisher=I'm Cordoba |language=Spanish |title=El pibe de la pensi\u00f3n |date=1 August 2012 |accessdate=23 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402181712/http://www.lmcordoba.com.ar/nota.php?ni=64071 |archivedate=2 April 2015  }}</ref> Dybala made his professional debut in the [[Primera B Nacional]] (Argentine second division) with his hometown club [[Instituto Atl\u00e9tico Central C\u00f3rdoba]] at age 17. In total, he played 40 matches with the club, scoring 17 goals.<ref name=SW>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/paulo-dybala/201072/|title=Paulo Dybala Player|publisher=Soccerway|date=23 October 2011|accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"dybala_player2\">{{cite news |url=http://www.institutoatleticocentralcordoba.com/index.php?option=com_joomleague&func=showPlayer&p=2&pid=59&Itemid= |publisher=Instituto Atletico Central Cordoba |language=Spanish |title=Paulo Dybala player 2 |date=1 August 2012 |accessdate=23 October 2011}}</ref> He was the youngest to score a goal, beating the record of [[Mario Kempes]]. Dybala was also the first to play 38 consecutive matches in a professional league in the country (again edging Kempes), and was also the first to score two hat-tricks in a season. Dybala also scored in six consecutive games, surpassing the previous record of four matches.<ref name=\"dybala_record\">{{cite news |url=http://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/dybala-pibe-records |title=Dybala, el pibe de los r\u00e9cords |trans-title=Dybala, the kid of Records |publisher=MundoD |language=Spanish |date=27 March 2012 |accessdate=27 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\n===Palermo===\n[[File:Paulo Dybala - 2015 - US Citt\u00e0 di Palermo (corner kick).jpg|thumb|left|Dybala taking a corner for [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]] in 2015.]]\n\nOn 29 April 2012, [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo]] president [[Maurizio Zamparini]] announced the signing of Dybala stating, \"We have got Paulo Dybala \u2013 the new [[Sergio Ag\u00fcero]].\"<ref name=\"dybala_aguero\">{{cite news |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/serie_a/palermo/2012/04/28-236116/Zamparini%3A+%C2%ABPreso+Dybala.+%C3%88+il+nuovo+Aguero%C2%BB |title=Zamparini: \"Preso il nuovo Aguero\" |publisher=Corriere dello Sport |language=Italian |date=28 April 2012 |accessdate=1 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304114849/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/serie_a/palermo/2012/04/28-236116/Zamparini:+%C2%ABPreso+Dybala.+%C3%88+il+nuovo+Aguero%C2%BB |archivedate=4 March 2016  }}</ref> Later the same day, however, Instituto's general secretary Jos\u00e9 Teaux stated that the man who had completed the negotiations with Palermo did not have the mandate to sell Dybala. Nonetheless, on 20 July 2012 Palermo released a press announcement confirming the signing of Dybala, who signed a four-year deal with the Sicilian club.<ref name=\"dybala_signed\">{{cite news |url=http://palermocalcio.it/it/1213/news/scheda.php?id=26948 |publisher=US Citt\u00e0 di Palermo |language=Italian |title=DYBALA HA FIRMATO |trans-title=DYBALA SIGNED |date=20 July 2012 |accessdate=20 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722191623/http://palermocalcio.it/it/1213/news/scheda.php?id=26948 |archive-date=22 July 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> According to the financial filing of the club, the transfer fee was \u20ac8.64&nbsp;million.<ref>U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo S.p.A. ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2013, PDF purchased from Italian [[Camera di Commercio, Industria, Agricoltura e Artigianato|C.C.I.A.A.]] (in Italian)</ref>\n\nDybala made his debut for the club in a [[Serie A]] match against [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]. He scored his first and second goal in Italy on 11 November 2012 when Palermo defeated [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] at home, 2\u20130.<ref>http://www.legaseriea.it/en/serie-a-tim/match-report/-/match-report/Palermo-Sampdoria/47894</ref> Dybala had his breakthrough season in the [[2014\u201315 Serie A]] where he scored ten goals in the first half of the season, forming a successful striking partnership with fellow Argentine\u2013Italian [[Franco V\u00e1zquez]] and being linked with several top European clubs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurosport.yahoo.com/football/serie-a/top-goalscorers.html|title=Football - Serie A - Standing - Top Scorers - 2014-2015 - - Yahoo! Eurosport|work=yahoo.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141228193641/https://eurosport.yahoo.com/football/serie-a/top-goalscorers.html|archivedate=28 December 2014}}</ref> He finished the season with 13 goals and 10 assists, which made him one of the top assist providers in the league.<ref name=\"espnfc.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/italian-serie-a/12/statistics/assists?season=2014|title=Serie A 2014-15  Statistics: Assists|publisher=ESPN FC|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Juventus===\n====2015\u201316 season====\nOn 4 June 2015, [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] announced the signing of Dybala on a five-year deal for a fee of \u20ac32&nbsp;million (plus \u20ac8&nbsp;million in add-ons).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/wps/wcm/connect/67da102b-88b0-4926-a001-60324f1a22fc/comunicato+04062015+dybala+eng.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=67da102b-88b0-4926-a001-60324f1a22fc|title=Agreement with Palermo for the acquisition of the player Paulo Dybala|date=3 June 2015|accessdate=4 June 2015|publisher=Juventus F.C.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150605120843/http://www.juventus.com/wps/wcm/connect/67da102b-88b0-4926-a001-60324f1a22fc/comunicato+04062015+dybala+eng.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=67da102b-88b0-4926-a001-60324f1a22fc|archive-date=5 June 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32870748|title= Paulo Dybala: Juventus sign striker from Palermo for \u00a323m|date=4 June 2015|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=5 June 2015}}</ref> He was assigned the number 21 shirt, previously worn by [[Andrea Pirlo]], who left the club that summer.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.goal.com/en/news/10/italy/2015/07/14/13576762/dybala-juventus-the-perfect-club-for-me\n|title= Paulo Dybala: Juventus is the perfect club for me|work=Goal.com|date=14 July 2015|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> On 8 August, he came on as a 61st-minute substitute for [[Kingsley Coman]] against Lazio in the [[2015 Supercoppa Italiana]]. He scored the second goal in the 73rd minute in a 2\u20130 win in [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/italian-super-cup/match/427876/juventus-lazio/report|title= Dybala and Mandzukic score as Juventus beat Lazio for Super Cup|work=ESPN|date=8 August 2015|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref> On 30 August 2015, Dybala scored his first league goal for the club in the 87th minute in a 2\u20131 defeat to [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legaseriea.it/it/serie-a-tim/match-report/2015-16/UNICO/UNI/2/ROMJUV|title=Roma 2 \u2013 Juventus 1|publisher=Lega Serie A.it|date=30 August 2015|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref> In his first 16 appearances of the season, Dybala managed six goals and two assists in all competitions, with a ratio of a goal every 151 minutes, which was superior to [[Carlos Tevez]]'s and [[Alessandro Del Piero]]'s goalscoring ratios in their debut seasons with Juventus. In the club's history, only [[Roberto Baggio]] maintained a superior goalscoring record in the opening games of his debut season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gazzettaworld.gazzetta.it/news/serie-a/juventus/dybala-best-players/|title=Dybala keeping pace with Juventus\u2019 best|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|author1=Ogo Sylla|date=16 November 2015|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nDybala scored his first career [[Coppa Italia]] goal in a 4\u20130 win over [[Derby della Mole|cross-city rivals]] [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] on 16 December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/77223/coppa-four-star-juve-crush-toro|title=Coppa: Four-star Juve crush Toro|publisher=Football Italia|date=16 December 2015|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref> On 23 February 2016, Dybala scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 2\u20132 home draw to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in Juventus' first round of 16 leg.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/80308/dybala-juve-can-do-it|title=Dybala: 'Juve can do it!'|publisher=Football Italia|date=23 February 2016|accessdate=23 February 2016}}</ref> On 15 March, it was announced Dybala would miss the second round of 16 leg of the Champions League against Bayern on 16 March due to an edema overload of his left [[soleus muscle]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://app.football-italia.net/?referrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.football-italia.net%2F81340%2Fdybala-marchisio-miss-bayern-juve#article/footballitalia-81340|title=Dybala, Marchisio miss Bayern-Juve|publisher=Football Italia|date=15 March 2016|accessdate=15 March 2016}}</ref> He returned to action four days later in a 4\u20131 away win over Torino,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/81592/line-ups-torino-juventus|title=Line-ups: Torino-Juventus|publisher=Football Italia|date=20 March 2016|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref> but was substituted after sustaining yet another injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/juventus/story/2848719/dybala-close-to-juventus-comeback-against-old-club-palermo|title=Paulo Dybala ready for Juventus return against old club Palermo|publisher=ESPN FC|date=12 April 2016|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref> On 21 April, Dybala scored two goals in a 3\u20130 home win over Lazio, which took his league tally to 16 goals in 31 appearances and also saw him score his 20th goal of the season in all competitions in the process.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/21-04-2016/juve-dybala-16-gol-meglio-baggio-trezeguet-raggiunge-ibra-platini-150318698836.shtml|title=Juve, Dybala a 16 gol: meglio di Baggio e Trezeguet, raggiunge Ibra e Platini|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=21 April 2016|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref> He finished the season as Juventus' top scorer with 23 goals in all competitions and 19 goals in Serie A, as the club celebrated their Serie A title victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/84331/juve-celebrate-sign-five?|title=Juve celebrate in the sign of Five|publisher=Football Italia|date=14 May 2016|accessdate=14 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/juventus-5-sampdoria-0-dybala-double-wraps-season-style#:jcIJ3WG-+s8bVA|title=Juventus 5 Sampdoria 0: Dybala double wraps up season in style|publisher=FourFourTwo|date=14 May 2016|accessdate=14 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n====2016\u201317 season====\n[[File:Dybala 2017 (edited).jpg|200px|thumb|Dybala with [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] in 2017]]\n\nFollowing the departure of [[Paul Pogba]] to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the summer of 2016, Dybala was offered the [[number 10 jersey]] by Juventus, although he turned it down, preferring to keep the number 21 jersey that he had worn during his previous season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/juve-dybala-turns-down-the-number-10-jersey-from-del-piero-to-po-729257|title=Juve, Dybala turns down the number 10 jersey. From Del Piero to Pogba it's the end of an era|publisher=Calciomercato|author=Marco Demicheli|date=5 September 2016|accessdate=6 September 2016}}</ref> Following manager [[Massimiliano Allegri]]'s switch to a [[Formation (association football)#4\u20132\u20133\u20131|4\u20132\u20133\u20131 formation]], the [[2016\u201317 Juventus F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]] saw Dybala operate in a deeper playmaking role behind the club's new signing [[Gonzalo Higua\u00edn]], which saw a decrease in his goalscoring output as he took on increasing defensive and creative duties.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/news/1371095|title=Why Barcelona will regret overlooking Dybala as Neymar's replacement|publisher=The Score|author1=Anthony Lopopolo|date=12 September 2017|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/juventus/story/3100793/juventus-paulo-dybala-says-i-dont-want-to-be-the-new-messi|title=Juventus' Paulo Dybala insists 'I don't want to be the new Messi'|publisher=ESPN FC|date=10 April 2017|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/juventus/111/blog/post/2963954/as-dybala-and-higuain-learn-to-coexist-allegri-must-get-creativity-from-rest-of-juventus|title=As Dybala and Higuain learn to coexist, Juventus need goals from elsewhere|publisher=ESPN FC|author1=Mina Rzouki|date=1 October 2016|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref> After struggling to score at the beginning of the season, Dybala scored his first goal of the 2016\u201317 campaign on 27 September, in a 4\u20130 away win over [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] in the [[2016\u201317 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/news/1112908|title=Watch: Dybala nets absolute screamer as Juventus crushes Dinamo Zagreb|publisher=The Score|author1=Gianluca Nesci|date=27 December 2016|accessdate=8 December 2016}}</ref> He scored his first [[2016\u201317 Serie A|Serie A]] goal of the season that weekend, on 2 October, in a 3\u20130 away win over [[Empoli F.C.|Empoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/empoli-0-juventus-3-dybala-122322896.html|title=Empoli 0 Juventus 3: Dybala, Higuain on target in comfortable victory|publisher=Yahoo.com|date=2 October 2016|accessdate=8 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April, Dybala scored two goals in Juventus's first-leg Champions League quarter-final fixture against Barcelona, helping the club to a 3\u20130 home victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39542727|title=Juventus 3\u20130 Barcelona|publisher=BBC Sport|author1=Phil Dawkes|date=11 April 2017|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref> On 13 April 2017, Dybala renewed his contract with Juventus until 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/101060/official-dybala-renews-juventus|title=Official: Dybala renews with Juventus|publisher=Football Italia|date=13 April 2017|accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref> On 3 June, Dybala started in the [[2017 UEFA Champions League Final|2017 Champions League Final]], but Juventus were defeated 4\u20131 by defending champions [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], missing out on the treble.<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/jun/03/juventus-real-madrid-champions-league-final-match-report |title=Real Madrid and Cristiano Ronaldo see off Juventus to win Champions League |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=3 June 2017 |accessdate=3 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n====2017\u201318 season====\nOn 4 August 2017, Dybala was named one of the three finalists for the Forward of the 2016\u201317 UEFA Champions League season award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2490056.html|title=UEFA Champions League positional awards shortlists|publisher=UEFA.com|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref> On 9 August, Dybala was confirmed to wear the number 10 shirt for Juventus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2017/dybala-10.php|title=Dybala 10|publisher=juventus.com|date=9 August 2017}}</ref> On 13 August he scored two goals in a 3\u20132 defeat to Lazio in the [[2017 Supercoppa Italiana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/13-08-2017/supercoppa-juventus-lazio-0-0-immobile-sfida-higuain-210982361279.shtml|title=Supercoppa, Juventus-Lazio 2-3, Murgia decide in pieno recupero|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=13 August 2017|accessdate=13 August 2017}}</ref> On 15 August, Dybala placed sixth in the [[UEFA Best Player in Europe Award#2016.E2.80.9317|2017 UEFA Best Player of the Year Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/about-uefa/news/newsid=2492844.html|title=Buffon, Messi and Ronaldo on Player of the Year shortlist|publisher=UEFA.com|date=15 August 2017|accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref> On 26 August, Dybala scored his first hat-trick in Serie A in a 4\u20132 away win over [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41062113|title=Genoa 2-4 Juventus|publisher=BBC.com|date=26 August 2017|accessdate=27 August 2017}}</ref> He repeated the feat on 17 September, in his 100th appearance for Juventus, scoring all three goals, including one free-kick, in the club's 3\u20131 away win over [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]], marking his second hat-trick in Serie A.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2017/dybala-masterclass-at-the-mapei.php|title=Dybala masterclass at the Mapei|publisher=Juventus.com|date=17 September 2017|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref> On 11 March 2018, Dybala scored a brace in a 2\u20130 home win over [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in Serie A; his first goal of the match was also his 100th career goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/11-03-2018/juve-udinese-dybala-fa-paura-dipende-tutto-noi-250851105440.shtml|title=Juventus-Udinese, Dybala fa paura: \"Dipende tutto da noi\"|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Jacopo Gerna|date=11 March 2018|accessdate=11 March 2018}}</ref> He made his 150th appearance in Serie A in a 0\u20130 away draw against [[S.P.A.L. 2013|S.P.A.L.]], on 17 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/spal-juve-talking-points.php|title=Spal-Juve: Talking points|publisher=Juventus.com|date=18 March 2018|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2018\u201319 season====\nOn 1 September 2018, Dybala made his 100th Serie A appearance for Juventus, coming on as a late second-half substitute in a 2\u20131 away win over [[Parma F. C.|Parma]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2018/08/30/serie-a-calendario-orari-come-vedere-terza-giornata.html |title=Calendario Serie A, la terza giornata: orari, programma partite e come vederle |publisher=Sky.it |language=Italian |date=30 August 2018 |accessdate=2 September 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/01-09-2018/parma-juventus-1-2-gol-mandzukic-gervinho-matuidi-290650448057.shtml |title=Parma-Juventus 1-2: gol di Mandzukic, Gervinho e Matuidi |publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |author1=Luca Bianchin |date=1 September 2018 |accessdate=2 September 2018 }}</ref> On 2 October, Dybala scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 3\u20130 home win over [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/128798/dybala-i-wanted-game|title=Dybala: 'I wanted a game like this'|publisher=Football Italia|date=2 October 2018}}</ref> In Juventus's following Champions League group match on 23 October, Dybala scored the only goal of the game in a 1\u20130 away win over [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/man-utd-vs-juventus/401859|title=Manchester United 0\u20131 Juventus|publisher=skysports.com|author=Pete Hall|date=24 October 2018|accessdate=14 December 2018}}</ref> With the arrival of [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], Dybala was often deployed out of position in a deeper role by manager Allegri during the 2018\u201319 season; as a result of this positional switch, as well as struggles with injuries, and difficulties with his manager, Dybala suffered a loss of form, and his goalscoring output decreased significantly, as he managed to score only five goals in 30 league matches, and 10 goals across 42 appearances in all competitions. However, Juventus managed to retain the Serie A title.<ref name=\"swap\">{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/11774327/paulo-dybala-to-man-united-how-juventus-forward-would-fit-in-at-old-trafford |title=Paulo Dybala to Man United: How Juventus forward would fit in at Old Trafford |publisher=Sky Sports |last1=Smith |first1=Peter |date=1 August 2019 |accessdate=24 November 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"plug\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thescore.com/chlg/news/1808823 |title=Report: Juve pulled plug on Dybala's move to Tottenham |publisher=The Score |last1=Nesci |first1=Gianluca |date=8 August 2019 |accessdate=24 November 2019 }}</ref>\n\n====2019\u201320 season====\nFollowing a disappointing 2018\u201319 campaign, Dybala was initially linked with moves to [[Premier League]] sides [[Manchester United]] and [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]], although he ultimately remained with Juventus for the 2019\u201320 season.<ref name=\"swap\"/><ref name=\"plug\"/><ref name=\"reason\">{{cite web |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/paulo-dybala-juventus-tottenham-man-utd-reason-he-did-not-want-join |title=Paulo Dybala reveals the reason he didn't want to join Manchester United or Tottenham this summer |publisher=FourFourTwo |date=9 October 2019 |accessdate=24 November 2019 }}</ref> Although he was initially not expected to start under the club's new manager [[Maurizio Sarri]], he eventually broke into the first XI and scored his first goal of the season on 6 October 2019, in a 2\u20131 away win over [[Derby d'Italia|rivals]] [[Inter Milan|Inter]], to help his side overtake the ''Nerazzurri'' at the top of the Serie A table.<ref name=\"reason\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49939525 |title=Inter Milan 1\u20132 Juventus |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 October 2019 |accessdate=24 November 2019 }}</ref> On 7 December, he made his 200th appearance for Juventus in a 3\u20131 away defeat to Lazio in Serie A.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://espanol.eurosport.com/futbol/dybala-disputa-su-200-partido-con-el-juventus_sto7568113/story.shtml |title=Dybala disputa su 200 partido con el Juventus |publisher=Eurosport |language=Spanish |date=8 December 2019 |accessdate=9 December 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:2017 FRIENDLY MATCH RUSSIA v ARGENTINA - Paulo Dybala 02.jpg|thumb|upright=0.6|left|Dybala playing for Argentina against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] in 2017]]\n\nDue to his family heritage, Dybala was eligible to play for [[Poland national football team|Poland]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]], but expressly stated that he feels Argentine and had always dreamed of playing for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/calcio/serie_a/palermo/2014/11/29-386072/Italia,+Dybala+dice+no%3A+%C2%ABGrazie+Conte,+ma+sogno+l'Argentina%C2%BB |publisher=Corriere dello Sport |language=Italian |title=Italia, Dybala dice no: \"Grazie Conte, ma sogno l'Argentina\" |date=29 November 2014 |accessdate=30 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402141637/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/calcio/serie_a/palermo/2014/11/29-386072/Italia%2C%2BDybala%2Bdice%2Bno%3A%2B%C2%ABGrazie%2BConte%2C%2Bma%2Bsogno%2Bl%27Argentina%C2%BB |archivedate=2 April 2015  }}</ref> Dybala stated \u201cI feel 100 percent Argentinian, I wouldn\u2019t be happy in a national team that didn\u2019t feel like mine, to hear an anthem that isn\u2019t my own, in colours that don\u2019t belong to me\".<ref name=noitalian/>\n\nDybala was called by the [[Argentina national under-17 football team|Argentina under-17 team]] to participate in the [[2011 Pan American Games|XVI Pan American Games]], but ultimately did not take part in the competition. On 19 July 2012, he received his first call-up for the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|under-20 team]], but declined the invitation.\n\nOn 22 September 2015, Dybala was called for the first time for the Argentina senior team by manager [[Gerardo Martino]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ole.com.ar/seleccion/Tata-pipon_0_1435656723.html|title=El Tata no est\u00e1 pip\u00f3n|work=Ol\u00e9.com|language=Spanish|date=22 September 2015|accessdate=23 September 2015}}</ref> but his first appearance was on 13 October 2015, coming off the bench to replace Carlos Tevez in the 75th minute during a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] match against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/world-cup-qualifying-conmebol/match/431629/paraguay-argentina/report|title=Argentina draw with Paraguay, still winless in World Cup qualifying|publisher=ESPN FC|date=13 October 2015|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref> In May 2016, he was omitted from Argentina's 23-man squad for the [[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/argentina/story/2876914/carlos-tevez-paulo-dybala-left-off-argentinas-copa-america-squad|title=Carlos Tevez, Paulo Dybala left off Argentina's Copa America squad|publisher=ESPN FC|date=20 May 2016|accessdate=31 May 2016}}</ref> Although Juventus insisted that they would not release Dybala for the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2016 Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]], he was included in Martino's 35-man preliminary [[Argentina national under-23 football team|under-23 squad]] for the tournament on 24 May;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/argentina/story/2880138/argentina-call-up-paulo-dybala-for-olympics-against-juventus-wishes|title=Argentina call up Paulo Dybala for Olympics against Juventus' wishes|publisher=ESPN FC|date=25 May 2016|accessdate=1 June 2016}}</ref> he was not included in the final squad for the tournament, however.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/90695/dybala-%E2%80%98no-barcelona-interest%E2%80%99|title=Dybala: \u2018No Barcelona interest\u2019|publisher=Football Italia|date=31 August 2016|accessdate=6 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 September 2016, Dybala was sent off in the first half of a 1\u20130 home win over [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in a 2018 World Cup qualifier for a second bookable offence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2016/09/03/57cb0456ca47413d418b459e.html|title=Dybala reassured by Messi after calamitous red card|publisher=Marca.com|date=3 September 2016|accessdate=6 September 2016}}</ref> On 13 June 2017, he set up a goal for [[Joaqu\u00edn Correa]] in a 6\u20130 away friendly win over [[Singapore national football team|Singapore]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.beinsports.com/en/football/news/singapore-0-argentina-6-dream-debut-for-gom-1/567940 |title=Singapore 0 Argentina 6: Dream debut for Gomez in Sampaoli's bold experiment |publisher=www.beinsports.com |date=13 June 2017 |accessdate=12 October 2018 }}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, Dybala was named in Argentina's preliminary 35-man [[Argentina national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Russia]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced?|publisher=Goal.com|accessdate=17 June 2018}}</ref> later that month, he was included in [[Jorge Sampaoli]]'s final 23-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/argentina-world-cup-squad-paulo-dybala-mauro-icardi-a8362096.html |title=Argentina World Cup squad: Paulo Dybala included but Mauro Icardi misses out on 23-man group for Russia |publisher=The Independent |date=21 May 2018 |accessdate=17 June 2018 }}</ref> He made his World Cup debut in Argentina's second group match on 21 June, coming on as a second-half substitute for [[Enzo P\u00e9rez]] in the 68th minute of an eventual 3\u20130 defeat to [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/21/sports/world-cup/argentina-vs-croatia-lionel-messi.html |title=Croatia Buries Argentina\u2019s World Cup Hopes in a Deep Hole |publisher=The New York Times |author1=TARIQ PANJA |date=21 June 2018 |accessdate=23 June 2018 }}</ref> This was his only appearance in the tournament, as Argentina were eliminated in the round of 16 on 30 June, following a 4\u20133 defeat to [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/43976007 |title=France 4-3 Argentina |publisher=BBC Sport |author=Emlyn Begley |date=30 June 2018  |accessdate=30 June 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/30/france-vs-argentina-world-cup-2018-live-score-lionel-messi-latest/ |title=Kylian Mbappe destroys Argentina to send Lionel Messi and co home in World Cup thriller |publisher=The Telegraph |author1=Sam Wallace |date=1 July 2018 |accessdate=1 July 2018 }}</ref>\n\nLater that year, he scored his first senior international goal on 20 November, in a 2\u20130 friendly home win over [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/lionel-messi-argentina-mauro-icardi-paulo-dybala-mexico-friendly-lionel-scaloni-video-a8644151.html |title=Lionel Messi void filled by Mauro Icardi and Paulo Dybala as Argentina enjoy friendly win over Mexico |publisher=The Independent |date=21 November 2018 |accessdate=21 November 2018 }}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, Dybala was included in Argentina manager [[Lionel Scaloni]]'s preliminary 40-man squad for the [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/copa-america-2019-argentina-announce-40-man-preliminary-squad-for-the-tournament |title=Copa America 2019: Argentina announce 40-man preliminary squad for the tournament |publisher=www.sportskeeda.com |author1=Nidhun Thankachan |date=19 May 2019 |accessdate=21 May 2019 }}</ref> Later that month, he was included in the final 23-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2019/05/21/argentina-copa-america-squad-roster-messi-aguero-dybala-scaloni |title=Messi Leads Argentina's Copa America Squad; Icardi Omitted |publisher=Sports Illustrated |author1=Avi Creditor |date=21 May 2019 |accessdate=21 May 2019 }}</ref> In Argentina's final group match against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] on 23 June, Dybala assisted Ag\u00fcero's goal in a 2\u20130 win after coming off the bench for [[Lautaro Mart\u00ednez]], which enabled them to advanced to the knock-out stages of the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en/copa-america-2019/video/copa-america-2019-qatar-0-2-argentina-match-r/1224974 |title=Copa America 2019 - Qatar 0-2 Argentina - Match Report |publisher=www.beinsports.com |date=23 June 2019 |accessdate=24 June 2019 }}</ref> In the third-place match against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] on 6 July, Dybala made his first start of the tournament, and scored Argentina's second goal in an eventual 2\u20131 win, to help his team capture the bronze medal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/copa-america/0/blog/post/3894006/messis-red-card-overshadows-argentinas-encouraging-win-and-chiles-end-of-an-era |title=Messi's red card overshadows Argentina's encouraging win and Chile's end of an era |publisher=ESPN FC |last1=Vickery |first1=Tim |date=6 July 2019 |accessdate=7 July 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nA quick, creative, elegant, and agile player, with excellent technical ability and a low centre of gravity,<ref name=\"evolution and devolution\"/><ref name=uefa.com>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=ita/news/newsid=2243658.html|title=UEFA.com's weekly wonderkid: Paulo Dybala|publisher=UEFA|author1=Paolo Menicucci|accessdate=1 June 2015|date=9 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calciomercato/13-12-2011/mercato-non-solo-tevez-juve-guarin-napoli-dybala-804018294216.shtml|title=Mercato, non solo Tevez Juve-Guarin, Napoli-Dybala|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|last1=Di Feo|first1=Giulio|date=13 December 2011|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.palermomania.com/read_articolo.php?page=11&id=1219|title=GATTUSO: \"C'\u00e8 tanto entusiasmo, colpito da Dybala. Dal mercato mi aspetto ...\"|language=Italian|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://corrieredelmezzogiorno.corriere.it/napoli/notizie/sport/2012/19-aprile-2012/palermo-occhi-puntati-paulo-dybala-2004143967576.shtml|title=Palermo, occhi puntati su Paulo Dybala|publisher=Il Corriere della Sera|language=Italian|last1=Lo Iacono|first1=Salvatore|date=19 April 2012|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Inter, ecco baby Dybala\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calciomercato/Estero/14-01-2012/inter-ecco-baby-dibala-arouca-fiorentina-81152124.shtml|title=Inter, ecco baby Dybala Arouca alla Fiorentina?|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|last1=Calamai|first1=Luca|date=14 January 2012|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref> Dybala is known for his powerful and accurate shots from outside the box, [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, balance, and close control in limited spaces,<ref name=\"Inter, ecco baby Dybala\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/paulo-dybala-juventus-serie-uefa-champions-league-real-madrid-argentina/|title=Names in the news: Dybala the crown jewel of Juventus|publisher=Sportsnet.ca|author1=John Molinaro|date=31 May 2017|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo\"/> as well as his ability to beat opponents in one on one situations and protect or hold up the ball for teammates with his back to goal.<ref name=\"Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/talent_scout/2012/04/29-236415/Paul+Dybala,+17+gol+per+stregare+il+Palermo+|title=Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo|publisher=Il Corriere dello Sport|language=Italian|last1=Chioffi|first1=Stefano|date=29 April 2012|accessdate=16 February 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141216091204/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/talent_scout/2012/04/29-236415/Paul+Dybala,+17+gol+per+stregare+il+Palermo+|archivedate=16 December 2014}}</ref> Due to his speed on the ball, positioning, intelligent movement, and ball skills, he excels during counter-attacks<ref name=\"Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo\"/> and at beating the offside trap when making attacking runs.<ref name=\"Scouting Report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/blog/scouts-notebook/78/post/2165111/scouting-report-palermo-paulo-dybala|title=Scouting Report: Palermo's Dybala to become better than Lionel Messi?|publisher=ESPN FC|author1=Nick Norrington|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=11 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"blank\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2017/matches/round=2000783/match=2019297/postmatch/report/|title=Juventus and Sevilla draw a blank|publisher=UEFA.com|date=15 September 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> A hardworking player, he is also known for his stamina and defensive contribution off the ball.<ref name=\"Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo\"/><ref name=\"elite\">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/paulo-dybala-is-juventus-striker-poised-to-join-lionel-messi-and-cristiano-ronaldo-among-the-game-s-a6827006.html|title=Paulo Dybala: Is Juventus striker poised to join Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo among the game\u2019s elite?|publisher=The Independent|author1=Peter Coates|date=22 January 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> Dybala is capable both of creating chances for teammates, as well as scoring goals himself, due to his vision, passing, link-up play, and ability to drop deep and play off of other players, as well as his powerful and accurate ball-striking ability from both inside and outside the area.<ref name=\"Scouting Report\"/><ref name=\"blank\"/><ref name=\"elite\"/><ref name=\"How Juventus miss Dybala\">{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/93796/how-juventus-miss-dybala|title=How Juventus miss Dybala|publisher=Football Italia|author1=Gaby McKay|date=2 November 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> Despite his diminutive stature, Dybala is also effective at scoring with his head, due to his acceleration over short distances, and his ability to anticipate defenders inside the box.<ref name=\"Inter, ecco baby Dybala\"/><ref name=\"Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/news/1278202|title=3 reasons Juventus outclassed Barcelona in Turin|publisher=The Score|author1=Gianluca Nesci|date=11 April 2017|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nA versatile [[Forward (association football)|forward]], he is capable of playing in any offensive position: he started out playing as a left winger for Instituto in Argentina towards the beginning of his career,<ref name=\"evolution and devolution\">{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/the-evolution-and-devolution-of-paulo-dybala-48639 |title=The evolution and devolution of Paulo Dybala |publisher=www.calciomercato.com |last1=Pandey |first1=Kaustubh |date=24 February 2019 |accessdate=15 September 2019 }}</ref> but since moving to Italy he has been deployed in a variety of attacking roles, including as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|main striker]], as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|centre-forward]], as a [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|supporting forward]], as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]], in a free role as a wide [[playmaker]], as a right-sided [[Forward (association football)#Inside forward|inside forward]], as a [[Midfielder#False attacking midfielder|false attacking midfielder]], as a [[Forward (association football)#False 9|false-9]],<ref name=\"evolution and devolution\"/><ref name=\"How Juventus miss Dybala\" /><ref name=\"Dybala tra Sivori e Tevez\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/18-01-2016/juve-dybala-sivori-tevez-messi-disse-di-noi-140306136476.shtml|title=Juve, Dybala tra Sivori e Tevez. E Messi disse: \"\u00c8 uno di noi\"|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|trans-title=Juve, Dybala between Sivori and Tevez. And Messi said: He's one of us|language=Italian|author= Mirko Graziano|date=18 January 2016|accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/italian-serie-a/12/blog/post/2685838/paulo-dybala-eased-into-life-at-juventus-by-allegri|title=Paulo Dybala coming along slowly at Juventus, but does Allegri know best?|publisher=ESPN FC|author1=JAMES HORNCASTLE|date=28 October 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"faccio tutto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/juventus/2016/11/25/news/juventus_dybala_a_tutto_campo_esterno_punta_trequartista_per_allegri_faccio_tutto_-152808183/|title=Juventus, Dybala: \"Esterno, punta, trequartista. Per Allegri faccio tutto\"|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=Timothy Ormezzano|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2017/02/16/juventus-dybala-ruolo-statistiche-verso-palermo.html|title=Dybala all\u2019attacco, manca solo la Joya del gol|publisher=Sky.it|language=Italian|author1=Claudio Barbieri|date=17 February 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> or even as an [[Inverted Winger|inverted]] [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]] on the right flank, where he is able to cut into the centre and [[Curl (football)|curl]] shots on goal with his stronger left foot.<ref name=\"Inter, ecco baby Dybala\" /><ref name=\"Paulo Dybala, 17 gol per stregare il Palermo\" /><ref name=\"faccio tutto\" /> He has also been used in a free attacking role on occasion, in which he is given licence to roam about the final third of the pitch, and either drop into the middle, or switch between the flanks, due to his ability to create from the left or cut inside and score from the right.<ref name=\"evolution and devolution\"/> Because of his work-rate and involvement in the build-up of his team's attacking plays, in addition to his goalscoring ability, former Juventus manager Massimiliano Allegri even deployed Dybala as an offensive-minded [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]] on occasion (known as a \"[[Midfielder#Mezzala|mezz'ala]]\", in Italian),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/112101/allegri-%E2%80%98juventus-can-win-or-draw%E2%80%99 |title=Allegri: \u2018Juventus can win or draw\u2019 |publisher=Football Italia |date=30 October 2017 |accessdate=28 January 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/allegri-reveals-why-juve-want-can-releases-dybala-update-42118 |title=Allegri reveals why Juve want Can, releases Dybala update |publisher=www.calciomercato.com |author1=Lorenzo Bettoni |date=5 January 2018 |accessdate=28 January 2019 }}</ref> and described him as a \"[[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box player]]\" (\"tuttocampista\", in Italian) in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/juve/2018/11/30-50539240/juventus_allegri_e_vero_che_dybala_segna_meno_ma_deve_fare_il_tuttocampista/?cookieAccept |title=Juventus, Allegri: \"E' vero che Dybala segna meno ma deve fare il tuttocampista\" |publisher=Il Corriere dello Sport |language=Italian |date=30 November 2018 |accessdate=13 December 2018 }}</ref> He has also operated in a [[Midfielder#Deep-lying playmaker|deeper playmaking role]] on occasion.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/19-03-2019/champions-ajax-juve-quattro-moduli-allegri-ma-qual-migliore-33042363174.shtml |title=Champions, Ajax-Juve: quattro moduli per Allegri, ma qual \u00e8 il migliore? |publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |date=19 March 2019 |accessdate=20 March 2019 }}</ref> Dybala is also accurate from both [[Direct free kick|free kicks]] and [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalties]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2325221.html|title=Messi and Pirlo in one? Dybala driving Juventus up Serie A|publisher=UEFA.com|author=Paolo Menicucci|date=18 January 2016|accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/juventus/2015/07/03-2140008/allegri_ha_gi_decisoi_tiratori_scelti_della_juve/?cookieAccept|title=Allegri ha gi\u00e0 deciso i tiratori scelti della Juve|trans-title=Allegri has already decided Juve's chosen set-piece takers|publisher=Tuttosport|language=Italian|author=Camillo Forte|date=3 July 2015|accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref> His playing style has drawn comparisons with compatriots Sergio Ag\u00fcero,<ref name=\"dybala_aguero\" /> [[Javier Pastore]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://palermo.repubblica.it/sport/2012/07/26/news/dybala_il_bomber_con_la_faccia_da_bambino_pronto_a_fare_innamorare_il_barbera-39741197/|title=Dybala, il bomber con la faccia da bambino pronto a fare innamorare il \"Barbera\"|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|last1=Norrito|first1=Massimo|date=26 July 2012|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref> Carlos Tevez,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/dybala-aims-emulate-tevez-success-juve#:vuI0ftcVq4w4MA|title=Dybala aims to emulate Tevez success at Juve|publisher=Four Four Two|date=7 December 2015|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> [[Omar S\u00edvori]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/horncastle-juventus-new-leader-why-paulo-dybala-should-be-given--105198|title=Horncastle: Juventus' new leader? Why Paulo Dybala should be given the No.10 shirt|publisher=Calciomercato.com|author1=James Horncastle|date=17 December 2015|accessdate=11 January 2016}}</ref> [[New Maradona|Diego]] [[Diego Maradona|Maradona]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/argentina/story/3141386/paulo-dybala-not-the-new-diego-maradona-not-as-good-as-people-say-pele |title=Paulo Dybala not the new Maradona, 'not as good as people say' - Pele |publisher=ESPN FC |date=10 June 2017 |accessdate=5 July 2018 }}</ref> and [[Lionel Messi]],<ref name=\"uefa.com\" /> as well as former Italian forwards [[Vincenzo Montella]],<ref name=\"dybala_montella\">{{cite news |url=http://livesicilia.it/2012/07/14/dybala-il-grande-colpo-lo-monaco-erede-di-montella |title=Dybala: il grande colpo, Lo Monaco: \"Erede di Montella\" |publisher=Live Sicilia |language=Italian |date=14 July 2012 |accessdate=9 May 2015 }}</ref> Alessandro Del Piero,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/15-11-2015/juventus-dybala-vola-ritmo-top-meglio-tevez-del-piero-130941261327.shtml|title= Juventus, Dybala vola a ritmo dei top: meglio di Tevez e di Del Piero |publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author=Fabiana Della Valle|date=16 November 2015|accessdate=26 January 2016}}</ref> and [[Roberto Baggio]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportnotizie24.it/news/opinioni/47340/paulo-dybala-come-il-primo-roberto-baggio|title=Paulo Dybala come il \"primo\" Roberto Baggio|trans-title=Paulo Dybala like the \"first\" Roberto Baggio|publisher=Sport Notizie 24|language=Italian|author1=Ivan Zazzaroni|date=14 December 2015|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> the latter described Dybala as the number 10 of the future in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/96689/baggio-dybala-future|title=Baggio: 'Dybala is the future'|publisher=Football Italia|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref> Widely considered to be a highly talented prospect in world football,<ref name=\"blank\" /><ref name=\"elite\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=2199779.html|title=Argentinian strikers making a mark in Europe|publisher=UEFA.com|author1=Majid Mohamed|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/fourfourtwos-best-100-football-players-world-2016-50-41|title=FourFourTwo\u2019s Best 100 Football Players in the World 2016: 50-41|publisher=FourFourTwo|author1=Greg Lea|author2=Andy Murray|author3=Tom Kundert|author4=Andrew Gibney|author5=David Cartlidge|author6=Alex Hess|author7=Simon Harrison|author8=Adam Digby|date=29 November 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beinsports.com/us/soccer/galleries/top-10-soccer-players-under-25/126641|title=TOP 10 SOCCER PLAYERS UNDER 25|publisher=beIN Sports|date=29 October 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2016/10/18/13079752/juventus-lyon-2016-uefa-champions-league-paulo-dybala|title=Paulo Dybala is already a superstar|publisher=SB Nation|author1=Conor Dowley|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/10108268/top-100-players-of-2015-where-do-lionel-messi-and-cristiano-ronaldo-rank|title=Top 100 players of 2015: Where do Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo rank?|publisher=Sky Sports|author1=James Walker-Roberts|author2=Patrick Surlis|date=31 December 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/paulo-dybala-has-quietly-become-one-of-europes-best-players-101816|title=Paulo Dybala has quietly become one of Europe\u2019s best players|publisher=Fox Sports|author1=Aaron West|date=15 November 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/argentina/story/2834867/dybala-proud-of-argentine-teammate-lionel-messis-praise|title=Paulo Dybala proud of Argentine teammate Lionel Messi's praise|publisher=ESPN FC|date=21 March 2016|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> in 2014, ''[[Don Bal\u00f3n]]'' named him one of the 100 most promising young players in the world born after 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercatonews.com/2014/11/19/la-top-101-dei-giovani-piu-promettenti-di-don-balon-quanti-italiani/|title=La Top 101 dei giovani pi\u00f9 promettenti di \u2018Don Balon\u2019: quanti italiani!|publisher=Calcio Mercato News|language=Italian|date=19 November 2014|accessdate=25 January 2016}}</ref> Despite his talent, however, his mentality, consistency, and leadership qualities have come into question at times in the media.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/club/juventus/111/blog/post/3180386/juventus-need-leadership-from-paulo-dybala-to-reach-their-goals |title=Juventus need leadership, consistency from Paulo Dybala to reach their goals |publisher=ESPN FC |last1=Rzouki |first1=Mina |date=15 August 2017 |accessdate=10 February 2019 }}</ref>\n\nAfter scoring a goal, Dybala is known for using his signature \"mask\" [[Goal celebration|celebration]]; regarding the gesture, he commented: \"My mask gesture isn't so much a goal celebration but rather a message. It's an ideal mask, which gladiators wore to fight. In Doha against Milan, after we lost Supercoppa, the idea of this celebration was born.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/131707/dybala-very-lucky-play-juve |title=Dybala 'very lucky' to play for Juve |publisher=Football Italia |date=7 December 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nDybala has several tattoos on his body: two stripes on his left arm, an Arabic tattoo as well as a crowned football on his leg.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tattooino.com/sportsmen/paulo-dybalas-tattoos/|title=Paulo Dybala's Tattoos|work=Tattooino|language=en-US|url-status=live|date=11 June 2018|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> On 21 March 2020, Dybala and his girlfriend, Oriana Sabatini, tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], amid its [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|pandemic in Italy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/151416/dybala-i-too-have-coronavirus|title=Dybala: 'I too have Coronavirus'|publisher=Football Italia|accessdate=22 March 2020|date=21 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51991426|title=Coronavirus: Paulo Dybala and Paolo Maldini test positive|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=22 March 2020|date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played on 8 March 2020}}<ref name=SW/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|[[Instituto Atl\u00e9tico Central C\u00f3rdoba|Instituto de C\u00f3rdoba]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Primera B Nacional|2011\u201312]]\n|[[Primera B Nacional]]\n|38||17||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2{{efn|Appearances in Relegation/promotion playoffs}}||0||40||17\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]]\n|[[2012\u201313 U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo season|2012\u201313]]\n